{"id": "40815", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40815", "title": "Den of Thieves", "text": "Den of Thieves is a side quest available in of . It is obtained from &lt;a href=\"General%20Stonehand\"&gt;General Stonehand&lt;/a&gt;, who asks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to try and root out the budding black market in the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; that she is certain has been the work of a thieves guild. She suggests starting by questioning the &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; merchant &lt;a href=\"Waizahb\"&gt;Waizahb&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuestioning Waizahb.\nOf course, Waizahb will deny having any involvement with such a group. The player can select one of several options; only the option \"\u201cFor your sake, I hope that\u2019s not true.\u201d\" is a guaranteed success to set up a meeting with Rhynwis. If they select the options \"\u201cI don\u2019t think so, and that\u2019s a good thing.\u201d\" or \"\u201cI\u2019ve not patience for your games.\u201d\", it will trigger a &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; check or a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; check, respectively; failure causes the halfling to flee and warn the thieves guild representative. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;, they also have the unique option to bluff Waizahb by threatening to curse her, which is an automatic success.\nIf successful, she will reveal that Gorion's Ward needs to speak to &lt;a href=\"Rhynwis\"&gt;Rhynwis&lt;/a&gt;, and will set up a meeting.\nTalking to Rhynwis.\nDespite what &lt;a href=\"General%20Stonehand\"&gt;General Stonehand&lt;/a&gt; says, questioning &lt;a href=\"Waizahb\"&gt;Waizahb&lt;/a&gt; is strictly optional; &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can simply speak to &lt;a href=\"Rhynwis\"&gt;Rhynwis&lt;/a&gt; automatically. There are three options for talking to her.\nFirstly, the player can threaten her by demanding she stop the thievery or pay the price. She will agree. The player can either attack her (she vanishes), ask for a cut of the profits (she will reveal the existence of a cache in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt;, containing &lt;a href=\"Harold\"&gt;Harold&lt;/a&gt; and minor loot), or demand that the guild assist the Coalition during the battle against the Shining Crusade (thieves make an appearance as allies during the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20the%20Camp\"&gt;Siege of the Camp&lt;/a&gt; quest).\nSecondly, the player can ask to join the guild. She refuses, reveals she recognizes them as the Hero of Baldur's Gate, and promises that the guild will disband before vanishing.\nFinally, the player can tell her outright that they want her to stop her operations. Her response varies. If Waizahb set up a meeting, options are presented as per threatening her. Otherwise, she simply agrees and vanishes.\nConclusion.\nOnce Rhynwis has been spoken to, Gorion's Ward can return to General Stonehand. If they explain that they only saw the guild's leader, but leaned on her to aid the coalition, then the general will throw in a bonus &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mind%20Focusing\"&gt;Potion of Mind Focusing&lt;/a&gt; to her rewards. Otherwise, they get the standard rewards array.\nGeneral Stonehand offers 300 gold pieces for the job. The player can either ask for a little more (increases to 500 gold pieces), demand 3,000 gold pieces (the general will chastise them, but still give them 500 gold), or accept the 300 as sufficient payment (+1 Reputation)."}
{"id": "7368", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7368", "title": "Den of the Seven Vales", "text": "The Den of the Seven Vales, previously called the Seven Veils, is an inn in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is operated by its owner, &lt;a href=\"Patricia\"&gt;Patricia&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0A group of adventurers staying on second floor will attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party if you respond negatively to &lt;a href=\"Mencar%20Pebblecrusher\"&gt;Mencar Pebblecrusher&lt;/a&gt; provocations.\nThe inn has two floors. The First floor is comprised of a saloon and a kitchen. It is where Patricia offers rooms for rent and beverages. An Athkatlan City Guardsman seems to be stationed and on duty in the saloon area. A number of commoners and nobles are in the saloon as well. There are numerous pick pocketing opportunities here.\nDon't forget to try some different Drinks at the bar (see the menu in the info box). You may get &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt; if you sample too many, but the rumors and immersion of various tidbits, scuttlebutt and chit chat can be worth it. So, spend a few golden coins, lubricate your parched throat, and hear the latest unofficial news as well. The more expensive the beverage, the better chance for the rumor quality. Many rumors are actually factual in whole or part.\nThe sleeping quarters are on the second floor, where Mencar Pebblecrusher's party resides. When you are observed, Mencar will address you and quickly insult your party - and unless you leave, will pick a fight. The dialogue options give you an \"out\" to avoid a confrontation, should you feel the need. Of course, you could attack without provocation with no reputation jeopardy, but will miss out on much dialogue. \nIf &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt; is in your party, it will soon be apparent that he and Mencar have some bad blood from a previous dealing with each other. Neither will back down, and violence is unavoidable, along with various excellent Dwarven insults.\nNotable loot.\nMostly equipment carried by Mencar and his gang (2nd floor), but don't neglect the Kitchen (1st Floor):\nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises all of the adventurers upstairs with new assigned AI scripts, weapon proficiencies and for the mage and familiar, spell casting and \"Smarter Mage\" behavior. You will find them noticeably a tougher challenge than the unmodified game. See each creature's article page for more details.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Isra%20NPC%20for%20BGII\"&gt;Isra NPC for BGII&lt;/a&gt; mod introduces Isra a female Paladin Cavalier potential companion. The mod begins the first time you visit the Inn (note that Isra was also available in BG1).\nThe &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Sphere%20Mod\"&gt;Planar Sphere Mod&lt;/a&gt; (as well as its spin-off, &lt;a href=\"Expanded%20Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Expanded Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;) has a major quest-related battle taking place in the saloon bar area."}
{"id": "7736", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7736", "title": "Denak", "text": "Denak is leader of four &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; who are found standing on the remains of an ancient temple in the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Wood\"&gt;Spider Wood&lt;/a&gt; area. The others in his group are &lt;a href=\"Diana\"&gt;Diana&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lasala\"&gt;Lasala&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Brendan\"&gt;Brendan&lt;/a&gt;. Unless the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; has &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt; in it, he and his comrades will become hostile after a brief dialog.\nDenak begins combat by casting &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; on himself, then switches to casting the offensive spells &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt; at the party.\nDialog.\nIf Edwin is in your party, Denak will speak to him and then the four wizards will disappear:\n\"Good day travellers. Mmmm, Edwin, I did not expect to see you so soon. I hope your business has been attended to Edwin, for if it hasn't, then you should do so soon. I think that Zulkir Nevron would be most disappointed if he were to hear that you failed. That is all that really needs to be said. Good day again, and goodbye.\"\nWhat follows is the dialog without Edwin in your party. In response to a threat, in what should by now be a familiar pattern, your options are pacifism, belligerence, or cowardice, none of which affect the outcome in the least.\n\"It is so sad to have met you this fine day. Normally, we would be quite ecstatic to have visitors, but in these troubled times we really do desire privacy. We just can't afford to have anyone knowing that we're here. That is why you must die.\""}
{"id": "37813", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37813", "title": "Deneld", "text": "Deneld is a military instructor for the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;, responsible for training new recruits to the cause.\nLocation.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten \u2013 Allied Siege Camp&lt;/a&gt; of , Deneld can be discovered in the south-central area of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;, next to the gates leading to the troll-pens and the broken eastern wall.\nQuests.\nDeneld must be spoken to as part of the &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Report%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Morning Report&lt;/a&gt;. If you ask him for the &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Report\"&gt;Morning Report&lt;/a&gt;, he will give it to you. Note \u2014 he does not have it in his &lt;a href=\"inventory\"&gt;inventory&lt;/a&gt; and as such, it will not drop if he is killed.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Foehammer%27s%20Blessing\"&gt;Foehammer's Blessing&lt;/a&gt;, he can be convinced to provide &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Stone%20Fragment\"&gt;Second Stone Fragment&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe also initiates the quest &lt;a href=\"Understanding%20the%20Crusade\"&gt;Understanding the Crusade&lt;/a&gt; to learn more about &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;The Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, having the party speak with &lt;a href=\"Sindret\"&gt;Sindret&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Zare\"&gt;Zare&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tristian\"&gt;Tristian&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ravoc\"&gt;Ravoc&lt;/a&gt; and then answer his questions. Upon completion, he will provide the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Crusade\"&gt;Ring of the Crusade&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47485", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47485", "title": "Denkod", "text": "Denkod is a thief who is found in the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;. He will approach the party upon sight immediately after they are teleported into the Thieves' Guild from the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Liia%20Jannath\"&gt;Liia Jannath&lt;/a&gt;. He'll give &lt;a href=\"Black%20Lily\"&gt;Black Lily&lt;/a&gt; a shout out during his dialogue.\nDialogue.\n\"What is this?! It seems like everyone's crashing in on the Thieves' Guild these days. First that huge armored guy, and now you! You better tell me what you're here about, and right quick, or you're in a lot of trouble!\""}
