{"id": "7463", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7463", "title": "Layene", "text": "Layene is a female mage and a member of the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;. When &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party accidently enter the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;Twisted Rune Hideout&lt;/a&gt;, they will be greeted by the lich &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar&lt;/a&gt;. After a brief conversation, he will summon Layene and three other members of the organization to dispose of the intruders.\nGameplay.\nThe mage will be invisible when she first spawns into the large circular chamber (normally north of the roundtable). Shortly after, a group of protective spells are instantly cast to include\n&lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf Layene can detect a party member, a spell trigger deploys and three more spells are applied to her, including: &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nShould any party summoned creatures be seen by her she will \"force cast\" a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; to try and banish them. If silenced, she will apply a &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt;. Most likely a &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; will also be cast by her in the first few rounds of the battle.\nAfter that, she'll attempt a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, and then while time is paused, cast a &lt;a href=\"Meteor%20Swarm\"&gt;Meteor Swarm&lt;/a&gt; on a detected party opponent. A &lt;a href=\"Gate%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Gate (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spell can also be attempted (she will be scripted to try and get a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; on herself as well). If the gate works, then a problematic &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;Pit Fiend&lt;/a&gt; will move toward and attack the party if any are detected.\nExpect a &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt; attempt. Another spell trigger can be applied later with &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnd a number of other attack and defense options will continue to be attempted, based on if she's able to cast and not disrupted. Various symbol spells, perhaps a &lt;a href=\"Efreeti\"&gt;Efreeti&lt;/a&gt; will be summoned, a &lt;a href=\"Wail%20of%20the%20Banshee\"&gt;Wail of the Banshee&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; and other dangerous spells.\nLayene is equipped with the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Magi\"&gt;Staff of the Magi&lt;/a&gt; and receives all of the passive benefits of this item. It can be looted from her corpse if you are victorious.\nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Layenne. She is a level 25 Conjurer. If the \"Smarter Mages\" component is installed, she will be a formidable Mage. Her memorized spells are mostly different than the unmodded, and can cast &lt;a href=\"Gate\"&gt;Gate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt;. Depending on your game difficulty selection, she has access to mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt;. If given enough time, she will use:\nLayene will likely be invisible from the outset (due to the Staff of the Magi), and will open up with \"previously cast\" buffs including &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, then a contingency with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Abjuration&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, Layene's arcane magic will be the SR versions.\nIf playing with the &lt;a href=\"Tactics%20for%20BG2EE\"&gt;Tactics for BG2EE&lt;/a&gt; mod, a different script is employed for spell use. The script is less dangerous in terms of damage dealing offensive spells but does a very good job of simulating Layene's use of the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Magi\"&gt;Staff of the Magi&lt;/a&gt;. After her considerable opening slew of protections (instantly applied while invisible), she will go through her scripted spell casting.\nAfter each spell cast, she is made invisible again as if she re-equipped the staff after performing an invisibility breaking action. This can be performed at least twenty times during the battle. Note she will be tough to target and may be the final foe still around after all the others have been defeated. With the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt; mod also installed, she will be protected with a \"Dispelling Screen \"and a &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;. With SR, Non-detection protects against all divination attacks. An &lt;a href=\"Oracle\"&gt;Oracle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; spells for example will not affect her invisibility.\nOne unusual opening move is her ability to cast a &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt; effect. This will immediately clear any cloud spells from the battlefield. She is also scripted to specifically cast &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Revanek\"&gt;Revanek&lt;/a&gt;."}
