{"id": "6572", "revid": "282665", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6572", "title": "Lazarus's missing spellbook", "text": "Lazarus's missing spellbook, \"Lazarus' Missing Spellbook\" in the original game, is a side-quest in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Lazarus%20Librarus\"&gt;Lazarus Librarus&lt;/a&gt;. Completing the quest will allow you to access his wares. He sells all mage scrolls as well as a few potions and arcane items. To get the quest you need to go to the &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Archives\"&gt;Arcana Archives&lt;/a&gt; in Saradush and talk to Lazarus."}
{"id": "6567", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6567", "title": "Lazarus Librarus", "text": "Lazarus Librarus is the owner and storekeeper of &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Archives\"&gt;Arcana Archives&lt;/a&gt;, a shop which sells magic-related items such as scrolls and potions. He can be first found in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;, but he doesn't sell anything &lt;a href=\"Lazarus%27s%20missing%20spellbook\"&gt;until his spellbook is recovered&lt;/a&gt;.\nLazarus is one of the few people who survives the destruction of Saradush by &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura's&lt;/a&gt; army, and the annihilation of the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; and civilians gathered there. He then moves to &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;, where he continues to sell the same items."}
{"id": "27332", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27332", "title": "Lea'liyl", "text": "Lea'liyl is a demon that is found on the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere%23The%20Abyssal%20Plane\"&gt;Abyssal Plane&lt;/a&gt;, which is located outside of &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;The Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;, once the sphere travels to this location after the quest &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Inside the Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; has begun.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party is within detection range of the demon, it will initiate a spawning spawns three additional support creatures nearby the Tanari, which are all hostile &lt;a href=\"Maurezhi%20%28The%20Abyssal%20Plane%29\"&gt;Maurezhi (The Abyssal Plane)&lt;/a&gt;. These creatures will cast an &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Animate Dead (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spell at the closest party member, and then at the second closest will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spell cast. They will then join in melee attacks.\nThe demon will open hostilities with a &lt;a href=\"Paralyze%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Paralyze (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability at the nearest player character. If a Mage or Cleric class is spotted, then it will launch the &lt;a href=\"Silence%2C%2015%27%20Radius%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Silence, 15' Radius (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability Tana'ri Silence. The demon will attack in melee combat for one round, then initiate a Tana'ri &lt;a href=\"Death%20Gaze\"&gt;Death Gaze&lt;/a&gt; at the closest opponent and then try a &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Touch%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Vampiric Touch (innate)&lt;/a&gt; ability at any in melee range.\nIf defeated, it will drop a &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Heart\"&gt;Demon Heart&lt;/a&gt;, a grisly prize that &lt;a href=\"Lavok%20Corthala\"&gt;Lavok Corthala&lt;/a&gt; has stated is needed to return the Planar Sphere to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike most demons, Lea'liyl is able to &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;. The demon inflicts 1d12 damage with its &lt;a href=\"S1-12M2.ITM\"&gt;elongated claws&lt;/a&gt; that are found at the end of its massive limbs, along with a strength modifier.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all the creatures in this area as well Lea'liyl in various ways. First, the mod has rewritten the Tanari class script, to improve the AI and tactical behavior. The Demon also receives the \"Teleport without error\" ability. A movement rate bonus is also furnished, and several spells dealing Hold, paralyze and electricity damage are now unable to affect the creature. The demon doesn't expend its innate abilities but may only utilize them based on a delayed time interval.\nThis demon is furnished a new melee weapon &lt;a href=\"BL3-12M4.ITM\"&gt;BL3-12M4.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, inflicting crushing damage instead of slashing."}
{"id": "2295", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2295", "title": "Leather Armor", "text": "Leather Armor is the cheapest and least-protective armor available. It offers an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 8 and it has +2 AC penalty to piercing and missile attacks, which means it offers no protection against these types of damage. It's often worn by &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt;s. It's sold at many weapon and armor stores throughout the games."}
{"id": "3768", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3768", "title": "Leather Armor +1", "text": "Leather Armor +1 is enchanted leather armor which offers a basic armor class of 7 and it has +2 armor class penalty against piercing and missile attacks. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and ."}
{"id": "6639", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6639", "title": "Leather Armor +2", "text": "Leather Armor +2 is enchanted and it offers an basic armor class of 6 to the wearer. It has a weight of 5 lbs. It is functionally identical to the unique armor &lt;a href=\"Protector%20of%20the%20Second\"&gt;Protector of the Second&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nDropped by.\nUnless otherwise stated, these items are worn as primary armor and therefore cannot be pickpocketed.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nDropped by.\nUnless otherwise stated, these items are worn as primary armor and therefore cannot be pickpocketed."}
{"id": "4044", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4044", "title": "Leather Armor +3", "text": "To see Leather Armor +3 from Baldur's Gate, see &lt;a href=\"Karajah%27s%20Life%20and%20Death\"&gt;Karajah's Life and Death&lt;/a&gt;.\nLeather Armor +3 is a heavily enchanted piece of body armor. Compared to &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;, this has armor class of 5, which is three points better and has weight of 4 lbs, making it 11 points lighter in weight. This item appears in and . It can be bought from the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer's Mart&lt;/a&gt; and from &lt;a href=\"Gorch\"&gt;Gorch&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt;'s guildhall."}
