{"id": "9117", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9117", "title": "Lich", "text": "Liches are powerful &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;magic-users&lt;/a&gt; that can be very dangerous to an under leveled or unprepared party. \nThis article page reflects the creature stats for a \"generic\" lich used in the and games, as well as the enhanced edition versions.\nThis particular cookie cutter game lich will be encountered in several areas, such as the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%202\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 2&lt;/a&gt;.\nAttention to the fact that the developers made it quite low-level for most liches in the Dungeons and Dragons setting. This won't affect its spell book variety, as it can still cast up to level 9 Wizard spells, but it will make it difficult for it to dispel any magic on the party, and conversely, easier for the party to do so in return - this is most likely done on purpose for novice players. Unfortunately for veteran players looking for the \"real thing\", the lich is somewhat hamstrung by this caster level reduction.\nThe InfoBox on this page reflects the creature used in the game for certain area \"High level spawn\" enemies.\nAbilities.\nMost lich immunities are derived from two undroppable items they have equipped. There is some overlap between the two. The InfoBox breaks these down.\nBeing formidable spellcasters, liches have access to and typically open battles with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; to make themselves nigh invincible. They can also cast powerful crowd control spells like &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Stun&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Fear%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Fear&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs undead, liches are vulnerable to anti-undead weapons such as &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Azuredge\"&gt;Azuredge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Earth\"&gt;The Burning Earth&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Daystar\"&gt;Daystar&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlmost all Liches are equipped with two undroppable items, one in each Ring slot. These items are used by the game engine to provide the lich with various protections and immunities to status effects, spells, specific damage types, weapon enchantment and other factors. The last item is the Lich's touch attack melee weapon. These items are:\nLich combat actions.\nThese creatures only conduct melee touch attacks as a last resort. They are not a high threat in this style of combat, unless playing a solo character and getting paralyzed. \nTheir THAC0 is not good enough to hit most opponents consistently, and they typically only get one attack per round with their touch attack.\nIt is more likely that a Lich will continue spell casting at point blank range in an unmodded game, rather than engaging in close quarters combat. \nLocations.\nNamed liches.\nSeveral liches in the game have unique names, and differing abilities, stats and sometimes much higher casting levels:\nHigh level spawns.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has an &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; of at least 2,000,000 points, liches, each time accompanied by two &lt;a href=\"skeleton%20warrior\"&gt;skeleton warrior&lt;/a&gt;s and two &lt;a href=\"greater%20mummies\"&gt;greater mummies&lt;/a&gt;, will spawn at the following locations:\nGeneral strategy.\nSee this article's \"Talk Page\" linked &lt;a href=\"https%3A//baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki/Talk%3ALich\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; for tips, and combat strategy thoughts that generally are effective against a lich.\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod doesn't use this generic 11-th level lich creature and disables it. \nInstead, it will replace the creature with a level 25 lich with a randomly determined specialty mage kit (Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer.\nSCS has nine different random liches to choose from.\nThe lich creature selected will have unique AI scripts and spell casting abilities will differ depending on the lich's assigned kit.\nThe SCS mod will improve a Lich's AI noticeably over the basic and unmodded EE versions of the creature. If the SCS \"Smarter Mages\" component is also installed, a Lich will be even more formidable, in that it will utilize triggers, sequencers and contingency abilities. This component also works with the game difficulty settings, and this could mean that a Lich will also have access, and use, Mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt;. Most SCS liches can see invisible creatures, and this cannot be blocked or dispelled. The exception is the Lich\" Nevaziah\" in the Lower Tombs as part of &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20Nether%20Scroll%20for%20Edwin\"&gt;Find the Nether Scroll for Edwin&lt;/a&gt; questline. \nSCS Liches gain a \"Fear Aura\" ability, an innate power they may use with a fairly large area of effect. A saving throw with penalty negates the &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect, but it is unaffected by spell level protections and magic resistance. \nSCS will also increase the accompanying creatures present with a spawned Lich as part of the High-level spawns (as mentioned above in the main article). There will probably be additional Giant Skeleton Warrior archers and a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt; if the PC is at or above 2M XP. At the highest difficulty a lich spawn is accompanied by &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Mummy\"&gt;Greater Mummy&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; and Skeleton Warrior Archer .\nSCS adds a Fire Lich to &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Yaga-Shura's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. SCS adds an apprentice lich with &lt;a href=\"Odamaron\"&gt;Odamaron&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the SCS \"More Consistent Breach\" component is installed, a level 5 &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; Spell can target a Lich, which it cannot in an unmodified game. However, SCS changes Breach to be blocked by all of the Spell Protection options such as Spell Shield, Spell Deflection, Spell Turning and Spell Trap.\nInstalling &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; will change the Liches spells to the SR versions. This is compatible with SCS by design. With SR, several of the \"standard\" favored mage and lich dueling tactics will differ, as there is no &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; option (it's now replaced by a \"Dispelling Screen\"). Both the AI and the party will have more options available to conduct a spell \"chess match\" with this mod installed.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Asylum\"&gt;Improved Asylum&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a lich to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%202\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 2&lt;/a&gt;. If the protagonist has 2M XP, the High-level spawn lich will also be present, right across the hallway.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a lich to the &lt;a href=\"Kuo%20Toa%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Western Tunnels&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "28137", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28137", "title": "Lich's Tooth", "text": "Lich's Tooth is an item in possession of &lt;a href=\"Deirex\"&gt;Deirex&lt;/a&gt; the lich, available during the &lt;a href=\"Intrigue%20with%20Jarlaxle\"&gt;Intrigue with Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt; questline only.\nGameplay.\nThis item is equipped in the Armor slot by Deirex, and thus cannot be stolen by pickpocketing attempts. Defeating the lich is the only method to gain this \"key\"."}
{"id": "56458", "revid": "283646", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56458", "title": "Lich (Crooked Crane)", "text": "The Lich can be encountered in and , as early as chapter 2.\nIt can be found in some sort of a tomb or crypt behind a secret wall panel on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Crooked%20Crane%20Inn\"&gt;Crooked Crane Inn&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates&lt;/a&gt; district.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party transitions to the new area, they'll observe a moderately sized rectangular shaped tomb of some kind - a macabre figure at the back stands before a large chest.\nThere is a stone sarcophagus in the center of the room as well.\nThe creature is a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt;, and if he's able to see/detect a party member it will croak out a hoarse whisper, saying:\nThe lich will now change from neutral to hostile and if able, release its preparatory protective spell chain.\nOnce hostile, the creature will attempt to cast spells to destroy any intruders in the crypt.\nSee the InfoBox for a summary of conditions and spell types that are possible.\nNote that this lich has no ability to dispel the party's protections or buffs, and it uses no spell removal magic. Use this to your advantage.\nIf the party is under some kind of invisibility, sanctuaried, or hidden, the lich will remain neutral and not even speak.\nIt is possible that a stealthy rogue could enter this crypt and investigate the chest and sarcophagus without alerting the undead mage - although it could expose the character as well, depending on what kind of action is taken. It is also possible to pickpocket this creature - if you dare.\nThe safest way to deal with the lich, is to be under the effects of a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Undead\"&gt;Protection From Undead&lt;/a&gt; scroll - with such a scroll the lich won't be able to find or target the interloping character and the monster could be killed with impunity with a simple magical weapon. Clearly this method is almost risk free, but don't expect it to be written into the annals of courage.\nAnother option is to simply get out of the crypt once it is known what is inside and stay out for now, especially if the party is not ready to face such a creature. Let's hope that the lich won't follow the party beyond its crypt.\nMaybe it's better to pay a visit to this lich when the party is better equipped, after having acquired &lt;a href=\"Azuredge\"&gt;Azuredge&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt; first, and use them to destroy it.\nShould the party destroy the lich, make sure any desired treasure is collected from the undead mage's robes and purse - and examine that big chest in the chamber too. Who better than a lich to have something worthwhile?\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises some aspects of the encounter with this lich. The first change is that one or more party members who initially enter the Crypt will not be able to leave this area until the lich is destroyed. Other party members who didn't transition with the first group cannot enter the Crypt until the lich is dead. \nWhen a party member tries to leave or enter the Crypt while the lich is still viable - A text will display, reading: \"An invisible wall of force has blocked the doorway.\"\nSCS has raised the experience level of this lich to 30. The mod also assigns a mage specialty kit to the lich, which is randomly selected at installation of the mod, either Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer.\nThe selected kit determines the available spells that can be cast by the lich.\nThe player's game difficulty selection and specific components installed will determine if this lich has access to mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; use.\nRegardless of what kit the lich has assigned, expect a wide variety of potential spells available, and that the creature will aggressively use dispel/remove magic. It can attempt more than one &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;, as well as various spell protection removers like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe lich will have use of prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; options.\nUnlike the base game's lich, this one can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56495", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56495", "title": "Lich (Purple Globe 4)", "text": "This Lich can be encountered in and games on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, when operating the &lt;a href=\"Globe%20Machine\"&gt;Globe Machine&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter the party presses the purple button on the Globe Machine and receives the fourth &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Globe\"&gt;Purple Globe&lt;/a&gt; - this lich spawns (along with a &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Lich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Elemental Lich&lt;/a&gt;).\nThis undead mage will appear and initially deploy protection buffs, and if damaged in some manner will further protect himself with a contingency.\nAfterwards, if able, he will cast spells as noted under the conditions listed in the InfoBox.\nThis lich can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;. \nFor some reason, this lich only has an 11th level mage experience level yet uses an 18th level spell caster script.\nThe lich will be particularly susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe lich's &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; scripted use is quite low powered by the time Watcher's Keep is typically explored by a party.\nWhen he is defeated, the lich's corpse remains on the ground, but no loot is discovered.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature.\nSCS doesn't use this creature (LICH01.cre) in the game at all - instead, it substitutes a random selection of a \"generic\" lich (nine varieties) to replace this creature, for greater diversity in gameplay.\nThe lich's experience level is always changed from 11 to at least 25, and will randomly assign a specialty kit at installation, either Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer.\nThe assigned kit will determine which AI script is used by the lich, and influence available spell choices, prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt;.\nExpect a much more challenging spell casting opponent, with the ability to recognize party buffs/protections, and the means to try and remove them.\nOn higher difficulty settings the lich will employ various mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56595", "title": "Lich Fear", "text": "Lich Fear is a nearly innate instantaneous aura that has a 30' area of effect radiating from the selected launch point of the spell, which is usually scripted by the AI as the lich itself. \nGameplay.\nDepending on the creature's script, this innate ability may be reapplied at a regular interval, such as once every several rounds. \nIt affects only the caster's enemies. \nThe effect is applied almost with no delay using SPIN536.SPL \"Fear\", but it is also labelled as \"Lich Fear\" in the script text. \nThe innate spell-like effect has no assigned spell school or secondary type and has a &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; of 0. \nEnemies in the Area of Effect not immune to fear effects must save vs. spell eith a -4 penalty or will &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; and aflicted with a -2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty lasting 1 turn. \nA failed saving throw will display a \"Panic\" icon in the victim's portrait. When under a panic effect, the victim will run about aimlessly with a yellow circle around their map screen animation. \nLich Fear is unaffected by magic resistance or spell level projections (such as Globes of Invulnerability or Spell Deflection). The effect cannot be dispelled. \nSpells that remove fear will bring the affected victim out of the Panic state, but the THAC) penalty remains until expiration. Additionally, a sound effect will be played if anyone is affected by the Lich Fear, and another will play when the spell expires."}
