{"id": "2866", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2866", "title": "Light Crossbow", "text": "The Light Crossbow is a two-handed ranged weapon and a weapon type in all of the \"Baldur's Gate\" series.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Light Crossbow is a lighter, smaller, and easier to handle variant of . Due to its size, it is easily concealable under e.g. cloaks, and it can be fired faster than the . Light Crossbows are a favorite weapon among &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt;, thus they are often frowned upon by the more &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;lawful&lt;/a&gt; inhabitants of the realms. &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Class%20group\"&gt;Warriors&lt;/a&gt;, who might desire a quick and small weapon with decent damage for ranged combat, and &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;s, who lack a &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; of twelve, also may rely on Light Crossbows.\nThe usual weight of 7 lb requires a Strength of 8 to be able to use the crossbow. As , crossbows are also a two-handed weapon. Light Crossbows can be readied to fire in only half the time their heavier kin requires, and they are even slightly faster than , with a speed factor of 5. However, they only have one attack per round, due to the relatively complicated process of reloading (with the exception of +1 APR variants eg &lt;a href=\"The%20Army%20Scythe\"&gt;The Army Scythe&lt;/a&gt;).\nWeight and speed are their advantages when compared to Heavy Crossbows, but these also bring a disadvantage: lack the +2 damage bonus that a Heavy one adds to every fired from it. However, a regular &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt; still delivers 2 more damage than an &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt; fired from a .\nEnchanted and unique variants may differ from these characteristics.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nForty-five Light Crossbows are available in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", sixteen are added by the \"\".\n\"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nAnother five Light Crossbows are made available for purchase in the \"\" expansion.\n\"The Black Pits\".\nThere are ten Light Crossbows available for purchase in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\".\n\"Siege of Dragonspear\".\nThere are forty-three Light Crossbows available in \"\"."}
