{"id": "4348", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4348", "title": "Lighthouse", "text": "Also called Seawatcher, the Lighthouse is a wilderness area on the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;. With shorelines at the north and the west it can only be left to the south, where an &lt;a href=\"Area%20South%20of%20Lighthouse\"&gt;archaeological site&lt;/a&gt; is located, and to the &lt;a href=\"Area%20South%20of%20High%20Hedge\"&gt;east&lt;/a&gt;, heading roughly into the direction of &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge\"&gt;High Hedge&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe eponymous but abandoned lighthouse can be found in a small walled area in the southwest, together with two desolate houses. To the north a bay with some sandy beaches cuts off the direct path to a cave, which is located on &lt;a href=\"sirine\"&gt;sirine&lt;/a&gt; territory and is said to hold the treasures of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Alaric\"&gt;Black Alaric&lt;/a&gt;, a pirate of legends.\nGameplay (community).\n~ Write your insights below \u2013 different from the Gameplay section above, you may use your signatures here; ~"}
{"id": "5008", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5008", "title": "Lightning Bolt", "text": "When a wizard calls upon a Lightning Bolt spell, he releases a powerful charge of electrical energy that immediately launches itself towards the target creature and bounces on walls. The &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Wand of Lightning&lt;/a&gt; can apply a version of this spell, which differs between BG1 and BG2.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single creature (including self) or interactable object (like a chest, or a potion laying on the floor) and casts the spell using the targeting cursor - which launches a lightning bolt projectile at that target. \nAny creature that has intersected the path of the lightning bolt projectile is exposed to its effects.\nEach time the stroke of lightning hits/connects with a creature it will inflict &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; scaled to the caster's level - although the victim is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells to reduce it by half.\nA lightning bolt that ricochets from a solid surface that strikes a particular creature more than once allows that creature another saving throw, and or a magic resistance check etc.\nThe bolt can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; can block the bolt from damaging the protected creature.\nAdditionally, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; will negate the spell.\nIt is possible that a single lightning bolt could bounce and ricochet and end up striking a particular creature, including the caster, as many as three times before it is grounded out and dissipated; this phenomenon is dependent on the area map's configuration as well the presence of solid objects that can affect the bolt's angle of incidence.\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nTreasure\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Lightning Bolt\" allows the caster to decide if the stroke will be a forked or single bolt variety. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its saving throw. See below for description:\nLightning Bolt\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Breath half\nUpon casting this spell, the wizard releases a powerful stroke of electrical energy that inflicts 1d6 points of damage per level of the spellcaster (maximum damage of 10d6) to the target creature. A successful saving throw vs. breath at -4 reduces this damage to half."}
{"id": "51292", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51292", "title": "Lightning Bolt (Mephit)", "text": "Lightning Bolt (Mephit) is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Mephit\"&gt;Lightning Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A lightning bolt projectile is launched at a single target in range. It will strike the target and inflict damage.\nThe innate ability has no saving throw. It can be blocked by magic resistance. The bolt also has a level 3 spell power, and thus could be blocked by spell protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The bolt will not bounce, unlike the arcane &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; spell."}
{"id": "11841", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11841", "title": "Lightning Mephit", "text": "Lightning Mephits are small, minor elemental creatures that are first encountered in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. They attack with their innate &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt%20%28Mephit%29\"&gt;Lightning Bolt (Mephit)&lt;/a&gt; ability.\nGameplay.\nA Lightning Mephit is fragile in comparison to other mephits in the game, presumably as they are initially encountered at the very start of SoA. They have low chance to hit anything in melee and they only have one attack per round. However, they do have a superior armor class as compared to other mephits, and an effective &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt%20%28Mephit%29\"&gt;Lightning Bolt (Mephit)&lt;/a&gt; innate ability. Within 2 seconds the mephit can launch this bolt at any creature in range, and then attempt another every three rounds of combat afterwards. It has an endless supply of these bolts.\nThe Lightning Mephit have no magic or physical damage resistance. However, electricity damage will actually heal the creature, and they are protected and immune to fire damage. The InfoBox summarizes their special abilities and immunities to certain status effects."}
{"id": "38859", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38859", "title": "Lightstone Symbol", "text": "The Lightstone Symbol is one piece of an ancient holy symbol of the deceased solar deity &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. It can be found hidden in an alcove in the back of a cell near the defiled chapel in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen this piece, the &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Ray%20Symbol\"&gt;Sun Ray Symbol&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Dawn%27s%20Light%20Symbol\"&gt;Dawn's Light Symbol&lt;/a&gt; are together in your party's inventory, they will automatically combine to become the &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Symbol of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. This piece and the Symbol of Amaunator are quest items needed to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the Deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47122", "revid": "277783", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47122", "title": "Liia Jannath", "text": "Liia Jannath is one of the Grand Dukes of the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; as well as a member of the Council of Four, along with &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Belt\"&gt;Belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Eltan&lt;/a&gt;. She will appear in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Palace\"&gt;Ducal Palace&lt;/a&gt; during the coronation of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter being ambushed by greater doppelgangers during the ceremony, you can give her &lt;a href=\"The%20Diary%20of%20Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok's diary&lt;/a&gt; to prove Sarevok's guilt (if Duke Belt was killed in the ensuing battle). Liia will then transport the party to the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAlthough Liia's spellbook contains spells up to the eighth level, she only uses &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; during combat. \nShe is more likely to survive if the mage spell Spirit Armor is cast on her in advance of the battle. If cast by an invisible companion this action will not trigger the dialogue.\nIf charmed, Remove Magic can dispel the haste and blur effects on the doppelgangers."}
{"id": "4218", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4218", "title": "Lilarcor", "text": "Lilarcor, also known as Lawrence Lilarcor, is an enchanted talking two handed sword. It's a +3 weapon in terms of enchanted weapons. It weighs 10 lbs and has a speed factor of 8. This weapon gives the wielder immunity from &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;charm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;confusion&lt;/a&gt;. Lilarcor requires a minimum strength of 14 to be wielded. Compared to other enchanted weapons +2 or +3, this item has a relative low value and it's a good quality weapon, but it's probably lowered because the sword may irritate the owner. It appears only in .\nLocation.\nIt is gained as a reward from the side quest &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20Riddle%20of%20the%20Sewers\"&gt;Solve the Riddle of the Sewers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\nThis dialogue can be engaged when clicking on the converse button while examining the weapon in the inventory menu. The status quotes are randomly picked, but the advice dialogue depends on the chapter. The sword does not give any advice in the chapters.\nWhen asking Lilarcor about its status.\nLilarcor: \"What's my status? Since when you do you care about me, unless I'm impaled in someone's guts? Oh, well, fine, let me think for a minute...\"\nYou get one of the four lines below:\nNote that if Minsc is in the party, he will respond: \"Minsc agrees! It would be the essence of epic heroing! Dead dragons should litter our path wherever we go!\"\nLilarcor: \"Ooh... I agree with the Rashemaar! Give me to him, will ya? C'mon! What a pair we'd make! Oh, me the brains with the edge, him the brawn with the hamster! A legend in the making...\"\nWhen asking Lilarcor for advice.\nLilarcor: The sword whistles, incredulous. \"Advice, eh? Well, besides working on your swordmanship. Besides that, I'd have to think.\"\n\"Hmmm... find someone rich, and kill them. Find someone richer, and kill them, too! Hack and slash your way to fortune! Woo-hoo!!\"\nQuotes.\nBattle quotes\nIdle quotes"}
{"id": "5847", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5847", "title": "Limited Wish", "text": "Limited Wish is a very potent spell that allows the spellcaster to potentially alter the current reality to a different one, in a limited or partial form.\nGameplay.\nWhen the character completes casting this spell, a 3D Djinni summoning animation renders adjacent to the caster, and when finished the Djinni materializes and the initiates a dialogue box to converse with the caster.\nWhile this dialogue occurs, all other creatures, including the party are paused in time until the dialogue is complete between the Djinn and caster - this spell can be used in the heat of battle, as long as the spell is finished properly without being interrupted/disrupted.\nThe caster can select certain actions with the Djinni, including:\nIf the caster selects a repeatable or one-time wish, another dialogue menu box is displayed with selection choices - along with a warning from the Djinni:\nSelect the desired wish, and the results will manifest on the map. With the wish completed, the Djinni departs the area in a dimension door animation.\nIf the summoner selects that they want to reconsider and not pursue the wish after all, the Djinni bids a final statement and dimension doors into the planes. The spell is finished.\nIn classic game versions, you can initiate talk with the summoned \"Wish Djinni\" with non-caster companions; In enhanced edition games, the djinni will only converse with the summoner if within the &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23R\"&gt;visual range&lt;/a&gt;. The djinni will disappear after 45 seconds have passed.\nFor some wishes, the summoner will instantly cast a spell that carries the wish effects; for some others, the game will create the desired wish effects.\nThe wish Djinni counts toward the summoned creature cap limits. If the party already has 5 on the map, the Djinni can't form and the spell will fail. \nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Limited Wish Wizard spell ages the caster 1 year per 100 years of expected lifespan.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod hasn't changed this arcane spell, except assigning it to the SR \"Universal\" spell school and by some internal scripting modifiers for better performance in the game engine. See below:\nLimited Wish\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Universal\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nLimited Wish is a very potent but difficult spell. It will fulfill literally, but only partially or for a limited duration, the utterance of the spellcaster. Thus, the actuality of the past, present, or future might be altered (but possibly only for the wizard unless the wording of the spell is most carefully stated) in some limited manner. The use of a Limited Wish will not substantially change major realities. The spell can, for example, restore some hit points lost by the wizard. Greedy desires usually end in disaster for the wisher. Lastly, the wiser the wizard, the better chance that he will choose the right wording. Wizards with low wisdom will more often than not meet with disaster when asking for a wish.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, there will be new wish choices available (Wisdom dependent) to upgrade a constructed golem or to upgrade certain rare components to even rarer ones, such as cold iron to mithral, or mithral to adamantine. This mod keeps adding content as you progress through BG2 and ToB."}
{"id": "24205", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24205", "title": "Limited Wish Adventure", "text": "The Limited Wish Adventure, also referred to as \"Help Vittorio collect his debt\", or \"Recover Dennis's mother's gong\" at different quest stages, is a side quest granted by the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish\"&gt;Limited Wish&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nPrerequisite.\nThis quest can be done whenever you feel like it, in either chapters 2, 3 or 6, but you must have the &lt;a href=\"Mercenary%20of%20Riatavin\"&gt;Mercenary of Riatavin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Delosar%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Delosar's Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; still alive, then with a &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt; of 10+, cast &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish\"&gt;Limited Wish&lt;/a&gt;, ask for a one-time wish and choose the adventure like none you've never experienced before.\nWalkthrough.\nHead out to the Bridge District and just outside the Delosar's Inn you will meet with a man named &lt;a href=\"Vittorio\"&gt;Vittorio&lt;/a&gt; who asks for your help in collecting money from &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt;. Agree to help him and follow him inside.\nCaptain Dennis and &lt;a href=\"Vittorio\"&gt;Vittorio&lt;/a&gt; are having a shouting match when you enter, seems that Vittorio stole and sold &lt;a href=\"Dennis%27%20Mother%27s%20Gong\"&gt;Dennis' Mother's Gong&lt;/a&gt; in order to buy ale. That sounds bad. Agree to help find the gong and onto &lt;a href=\"Roger%20the%20Fence\"&gt;Roger the Fence&lt;/a&gt; who you will find in the southern part of the sewers beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nRoger doesn't have the gong and will only tell you where it is until you take care of a local &lt;a href=\"Sea%20Troll\"&gt;Sea Troll&lt;/a&gt; , which you may have already dealt with. Talk to Roger again after the deed and &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt; will be marked on your map.\nOnce there, head left to find the &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Mound\"&gt;Troll Mound&lt;/a&gt; . &lt;a href=\"Grae\"&gt;Grae&lt;/a&gt;, the troll shaman just outside of the mound will attack you at the mention of the gong, when it gets close to death it offers the gong's whereabouts in exchange for its life (if you kill it before the fight stops to start the conversation, the ogre magi does not appear), the gong is in possession of &lt;a href=\"Drush\"&gt;Drush&lt;/a&gt;, an Ogre Mage in a tower to the northeast of here.\nWander north, then east, across the bridge to find a big house, just south of it is the &lt;a href=\"Ogre%27s%20Tower\"&gt;tower&lt;/a&gt; . This Ogre Mage inside is quite the peaceable sort and is very willing to trade the gong for a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt;, if you have it (). Oh, and don't mind the smell because here you will also find &lt;a href=\"Belm\"&gt;Belm&lt;/a&gt;, if you haven't already looted the tower before.\nReturn to the Bridge District and give the gong back, everyone seems satisfied, except Vittorio, because Captain Dennis still hasn't given him money to pay his bar tab. Dennis agrees to pay half and tells Vittorio to beat it. Afterwards the party gets a reward:"}
{"id": "16248", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16248", "title": "Lin", "text": "Lin is a shadow thief that is being tortured by &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; which can potentially become your own &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild%20Stronghold\"&gt;guildhall&lt;/a&gt; later if you're a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; and have completed &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt; side quest, but unfortunately Lin is killed before that.\nIf you you and speak with the man - the text displays \"This man has been tortured severely and is presently unconscious.\""}
