{"id": "15570", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15570", "title": "Llynis", "text": "Llynis is upstairs in his rented room on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSpeak with Llynis to have a discussion with him. He won't initiate dialogue.\nHe'll mention he was startled by you and thought it might be a ghost. You can ask him about that if interested.\nHowever, if the party is here because of the &lt;a href=\"Put%20the%20Spirit%20of%20the%20Child%20Wellyn%20to%20Rest\"&gt;Put the Spirit of the Child Wellyn to Rest&lt;/a&gt; quest, then you'll have more dialogue selections. And several more options as what to do about your quest, in a peaceful or not so peaceful manner.\nA locked drawer in Llynis's room contains scrolls of &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Luck%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Luck&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Fear\"&gt;Resist Fear&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Emerald\"&gt;Emerald&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Greenstone%20Ring\"&gt;Greenstone Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote.\nLlynis's alignment in the original game is True Neutral but changed to LE in the Enhanced Edition.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; updates this creature with a default Thief SCS AI script for smarter tactical behavior. His weapon proficiencies are revised as well to match up with a rogue's experience level and weapon choice. He may try turning invisible with his mod supplied potions and perform &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; attacks."}
{"id": "8197", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8197", "title": "Lobar", "text": "Lobar is the owner of the &lt;a href=\"Low%20Lantern\"&gt;Low Lantern&lt;/a&gt; which is a floating gambling hall and brothel docked in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He'll give a respectable, and yet sometimes witty, response that's all business to any dialogue choice you select. Other than that he doesn't have much of anything to offer. He can be killed without any consequences.\nDialogue.\n\"Welcome to the Low Lantern, my friends. I trust you will enjoy your stay, and sample much of our lively fare.\"\nAfter responding to any one of the dialogue choices you choose, he'll simple reply with the following when further conversation is attempted. "}
{"id": "11306", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11306", "title": "Locate a Caretaker for the Orphan, Risa", "text": "Locate a Caretaker for the Orphan, Risa is a side quest in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Graveyard%20District\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nDuring the day (between 6:30 and 9:30, and between 12:30 and 15:30), you can find Dawnlord &lt;a href=\"Arenthis\"&gt;Arenthis&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Lathander\"&gt;Lathander&lt;/a&gt; standing with an orphan girl named &lt;a href=\"Risa\"&gt;Risa&lt;/a&gt; outside of the easternmost tomb.\nHe explains that \"Risa doesn't talk much since the recent death of her parents\" and \"there is very little that can be done for her...other than to put her into an orphanage.\" However, Arenthis is \"sure it will do her no good\" as \"she is so shy and sad\" and although he \"would not ask you to care for her...might you know of someone who would make a suitable guardian?\"\nYou have two options with which you may reply. In either case, a new entry appears in your Journal whether you help them or not.\"I ran into a priest of Lathander named Arenthis, who is looking for a guardian for his young charge, Risa. If there were only someone noble enough who were free and willing to take care of the girl, I would recommend them.\""}
{"id": "14457", "revid": "53800764", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14457", "title": "Lock of Hair from Kirinhale", "text": "The Lock of Hair from Kirinhale can be either looted from &lt;a href=\"Kirinhale\"&gt;Kirinhale&lt;/a&gt;'s corpse or given freely to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. If looted, it may traded to the thief &lt;a href=\"Riggilo\"&gt;Riggilo&lt;/a&gt; for a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Cloud%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Cloud Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;. If received, you may similarly gift it to the same thief in order to set Kirinhale free. There are no other known uses for this item, as it pointedly is not a &lt;a href=\"Lock%20of%20Nymph%27s%20Hair\"&gt;Lock of Nymph's Hair&lt;/a&gt;. It may be identified, but there is little reason to do so, other than to ascertain the description.\nIt can be sold to &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt; for 250gp, but it cannot be woven into a &lt;a href=\"Nymph%20Cloak\"&gt;Nymph Cloak&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be sold at &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt; or to &lt;a href=\"Thalantyr%20the%20Conjurer\"&gt;Thalantyr the Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge%20Estate\"&gt;High Hedge&lt;/a&gt; for the same 250gp."}
