{"id": "49175", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49175", "title": "Loren", "text": "Loren is a boy in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; who is a descendant of &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; who founded the &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nHe is being tormented by 'voices' in his mind caused by a spirit of chaos - an evil influence that the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20of%20the%20Grove\"&gt;Spirit of the Grove&lt;/a&gt; wishes removed from the boy's mind, and then destroyed to restore the natural balance.\nAs part of the &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, the party druid will be directed by the Spirit of the Grove to assist Loren expel the evil spirit of &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20%28Creature%29\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. The party must force the spirit to reveal its true essence, and then destroy its physical form.\nUpon first speaking to Loren, he asks, \"Are you the one who has come to... to kill me? I hear you... whispering all the time. I just want it to stop! I want it all to stop!!\"\nThe player must exorcise the evil spirit to face you in more than a battle of wills. If Chaos has been defeated, Loren will remark:\n\"I have spoken with... the Spirit. I want to become a druid, I guess. It said that I will protect the Grove when you have moved on... that I have a destiny, here.\""}
{"id": "50299", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50299", "title": "Loron's Return (Ajoc's minimod restored)", "text": "Loren's Return is a quest mod for and &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition%20Trilogy\"&gt;EET&lt;/a&gt; based on the old &lt;a href=\"Ajoc%27s%20Minimod\"&gt;Ajoc's Minimod&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe quest begins when Brus (Gaelen Bayles nephew) tells you about a mage in the Council of Six building in the Government District of Athkatla.\nFor more information see the links."}
{"id": "8647", "revid": "283381", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8647", "title": "Lothander", "text": "Lothander is a &lt;a href=\"Thief%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; who is enspelled by a &lt;a href=\"geas\"&gt;geas&lt;/a&gt; and forced to help &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; poison &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter you have encountered Marek and Lothander in the eastern section of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, the Marek and Lothander quest will begin once you've come across Lothander in the &lt;a href=\"Marketplace%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;marketplace&lt;/a&gt; section of &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will inform you that you've been poisoned and if you agree to help him remove the geas, he will in turn provide you with his half of the antidote and the location of Marek, who possesses the other half of the required antidote. WARNING: If you kill him outright, Lothander will not drop his antidote, and Marek will not spawn at the Blushing Mermaid, so you have to help him."}
{"id": "34132", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34132", "title": "Lothander's Potion of Antidote", "text": "Lothander's Potion of Antidote is a quest item in the the &lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt; quest in . &lt;a href=\"Lothander\"&gt;Lothander&lt;/a&gt; tasks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with procuring a &lt;a href=\"Geas%20Removal%20Scroll\"&gt;Geas Removal Scroll&lt;/a&gt;; he will be in the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars&lt;/a&gt; and exchange his potion for the scroll. Gorion's Ward still needs to find &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Marek%27s%20Potion%20of%20Antidote\"&gt;Marek's Potion of Antidote&lt;/a&gt; to cure the poison.\nIn the original &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, Lothander would give the player a &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;potion of antidote&lt;/a&gt; instead."}
{"id": "8620", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8620", "title": "Louise", "text": "Louise and her twin sister &lt;a href=\"Laerta\"&gt;Laerta&lt;/a&gt; are found in the master bedroom of their &lt;a href=\"Laerta%20and%20Louise%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; which is located in &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. They are scared by a 'bogeyman' who spies on them at night. Solving their &lt;a href=\"Laerta%20and%20Louise\"&gt;dilemma&lt;/a&gt; gives the party 1000 XP and a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil&lt;/a&gt; scroll."}
{"id": "29703", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29703", "title": "Loup Garou", "text": "Loup Garou are a more powerful sub-breed of the more common &lt;a href=\"werewolf\"&gt;werewolf&lt;/a&gt; strain of &lt;a href=\"lycanthropy\"&gt;lycanthropy&lt;/a&gt;, analogous to the &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Wolfwere\"&gt;Greater Wolfwere&lt;/a&gt;s that rule over the packs of &lt;a href=\"wolfwere\"&gt;wolfwere&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCombat.\nUnlike their &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Wolfwere\"&gt;Greater Wolfwere&lt;/a&gt; counterparts, Loup Garou cannot regenerate. Moreover, immunity to all but is solely found in Selaad Gan's Loup Garou form (and, technically, Gorion's Ward's party when they change), with both Kaishas Gan's and Baresh's forms only being immune to normal weapons. For a detailed view of their stats, please refer to their individual articles, as they vary quite a bit (eg Kaishas has the best &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, Baresh has the best saves and Selaad has the best ability scores, AC and APR).\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt; spell and &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Paralyzation\"&gt;Wand of Paralyzation&lt;/a&gt; are capable of paralyzing Loup Garou, which temporarily negates their ability to fight back. The &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Polymorphing\"&gt;Wand of Polymorphing&lt;/a&gt; is also effective against them, having the potential to end combat in a single round.\nMeta.\nLoup Garou originate from the AD&amp;D tabletop roleplaying game, and debuted as part of the Ravenloft setting. Defined as a more powerful breed of &lt;a href=\"werewolf\"&gt;werewolf&lt;/a&gt;, there were actually two different strains of Loup Garou: the Lowland (shapeshifts into a &lt;a href=\"worg\"&gt;worg&lt;/a&gt;, vulnerable to silver) and the Mountain (shapeshifts into a &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Wolf\"&gt;Dire Wolf&lt;/a&gt;, vulnerable to gold). The Loup Garou would also make it into D&amp;D 3rd Edition in the Ravenloft sourcebooks \"Denizens of Darkness\" (for 3.0) and Denizens of Dread (for 3.5)."}
{"id": "9629", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9629", "title": "Love", "text": "Love is one of four dwarven &lt;a href=\"warders\"&gt;warders&lt;/a&gt; guarding the way to &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Two%29\"&gt;Labyrinth Level Two&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. She must be given a &lt;a href=\"Bottle%20of%20Wine%20%28Durlag%27s%20Tower%29\"&gt;bottle of wine&lt;/a&gt; to solve her riddle. She will only accept the wine after the other three riddles have been solved.\nLove drops the bottle of wine where she is standing, next to the entrance to level two, while she drops the wardstone and the bastard sword where she dies."}
