{"id": "22507", "revid": "274195", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22507", "title": "M'Khiin Grubdoubler (quest)", "text": "Having &lt;a href=\"M%27Khiin%20Grubdoubler\"&gt;M'Khiin&lt;/a&gt; in company will enable or extend the experiences of several encounters in \"\".\n&lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo the west of &lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Announcer\"&gt;Announcer&lt;/a&gt; in , there is a pile of four bodies. If M\u2019Khiin is in your group, she will be able to summon the spirits of the goblins &lt;a href=\"R%27gosz%20the%20Puke\"&gt;R'gosz the Puke&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"D%27mak%20Greatgas\"&gt;D'mak Greatgas&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sot%20Darkoozing\"&gt;Sot Darkoozing&lt;/a&gt;, and their apparent leader, &lt;a href=\"Gar%20Fouleye\"&gt;Gar Fouleye&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey express disgust upon learning it's M'Khiin, who they revile for stories of her abandoning her tribe and it can be learned that Fouleye killed D'mak for no particular reason, after which the Puke killed heim and Sot both, sustaining mortal wounds while doing so. Not long after, the ghost of \"the Puke\" finally loses control and the spirits attack the party but combat will end when any one of the spirits would normally be killed.\nWhen finally beaten, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must decide their fate, and if M'Khiin is given the choice or the spirits are threatened with destruction, they offer the location of a secret cache in exchange for mercy.\nWarning: If they are dismissed without threat, they will not give the location of the cache and it will never be accessible.\nIf the party then travels to the west bank of the river, north of the bridge, they will find numerous traps, as well as a bush with a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potion of Freedom&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;, 2 &lt;a href=\"sling\"&gt;sling&lt;/a&gt;s, 19 &lt;a href=\"bullet\"&gt;bullet&lt;/a&gt;s, , and most importantly, &lt;a href=\"Blightbringer\"&gt;Blightbringer&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter completing &lt;a href=\"Wynan%20Hess\"&gt;Wynan Hess&lt;/a&gt;'s quest at &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 9, talk to &lt;a href=\"Jegg%20Hillcarver\"&gt;Jegg Hillcarver&lt;/a&gt; to craft a new &lt;a href=\"Jegg%27s%20Leathers\"&gt;Jegg's Leathers&lt;/a&gt; for M\u2019Khiin.\n&lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt;.\nNorth of your starting zone on &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; area in Chapter 10, you'll meet a raid band led by &lt;a href=\"Battuks\"&gt;Battuks&lt;/a&gt;, you can squeeze 12000 more &lt;a href=\"Experience%20tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; out of this encounter if you have M\u2019Khiin interact with them in group.\n&lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt;.\nA pile of equipment will appear where you fight the undead hordes at &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt; if you travel with M\u2019Khiin there in Chapter 10. M\u2019Khiin will be able to equip two of four items depending on which path she chooses: the shamanic path for &lt;a href=\"The%20Soulherder%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Soulherder's Staff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Ghostdreamers%27%20Robe\"&gt;Ghostdreamers' Robe&lt;/a&gt;; the warrior path for &lt;a href=\"Axe%20of%20Kruntur\"&gt;Axe of Kruntur&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Kruntur%27s%20Armor\"&gt;Kruntur's Armor&lt;/a&gt;. Note the choice just determines which two items M\u2019Khiin can use, it won't affect her actual status."}
{"id": "49365", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49365", "title": "MAGE01.ITM", "text": "MAGE01.ITM is an undroppable Ring of Invisibility equipped to various NPCs in the .\nIts player-accessible version is Ring05.itm.\nEffects.\nIts single effect is &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 20), on the wearer, of type \"Normal\" (i.e., not &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;). It can be dispelled and does not bypass resistance. The actual result of a creature wearing this ring will provide the creature with invisibility at the start of any potential conflict, without having to cast a spell or otherwise initiate some kind of ability to attain invisibility. Once the creature performs an action that breaks the invisibility, the item will not function again. This item is designed for opponents or to shield a sprite from view in the game. Further attempts at invisibility by that creature will be scripted or performed by spell cast or item use (such as a potion).\nNote that some creatures that are always invisible, such as the &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt; use this item to attain invisibility at the outset of combat only. Within the actual creature file are additional invisibility &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; assignments to retain the invisibility even if they perform an invisibility breaking action, and to ensure that it cannot be dispelled.\nCreatures.\nThere are many creatures that equip this ring. Notable NPCs include:"}
{"id": "56674", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56674", "title": "MAGE03.ITM", "text": "MAGE03.ITM is an undroppable Ring equipped to various NPCs in the , for example, &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; wears one of these.\nGameplay.\nThe item is usually added to one of the creature's ring slots.\nThe item casts a spell upon the wearer that has no expiration, just by having it equipped.\nThe spell is OHWI212.spl, which is a version of the wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, except it provides 4 images only.\nThis spell behaves the same as the ordinary wizard spell, except for its duration.\nThe spell can be removed by certain divination, a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, and the images can be destroyed through combat actions as usual.\nOnce all the images are destroyed, the ring won't replace them or cast another spell upon the wearer, and thus, the ring serves as a method for the game to protect a creature at the outset of combat without the creature needing to cast the spell upon itself.\nThe ring has no other abilities."}
{"id": "56675", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56675", "title": "MAGE05.ITM", "text": "MAGE05.ITM is an undroppable Ring equipped to various NPCs in the , for example, &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; wears one of these.\nGameplay.\nThe item is usually added to one of the creature's ring slots.\nThe item provides immunity and protection from a number of &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; and specific spells - permanently.\nThe protections conferred cannot be removed, dispelled or otherwise taken down.\nThis item is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Edventar%27s%20Gift\"&gt;Edventar's Gift&lt;/a&gt; ring that can be obtained by the player, however, it has some differences, including no adjustments or blocking of movement rate modifiers or the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;, nor a traditional &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28status%20effect%29\"&gt;Free Action (status effect)&lt;/a&gt;.\nSee the InfoBox for a breakdown of immunities and protections.\nThe ring has no other abilities."}
{"id": "49442", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49442", "title": "MAGE06.ITM", "text": "MAGE06.ITM is an undroppable ring equipped to certain creatures to primarily to increase moment rate, but it also grants all normal haste modifiers as well.\nEffects.\nIt is a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; but &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;non-enchanted&lt;/a&gt; ring that grants a &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Normal Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; (Op Code 16). The effect can be dispelled and does not bypass resistance."}
{"id": "56676", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56676", "title": "MAGEBRAC.ITM", "text": "MAGEBRAC.ITM is an undroppable Bracer equipped to various NPCs in the , for example, &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; wears this item.\nGameplay.\nThe item is usually added to the creature's glove/gauntlet slot.\nThe item casts a spell upon the wearer that has a 5-turn duration, just by having it equipped.\nThe spell is OHWI311.spl, which is a version of the wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell behaves the same as the ordinary wizard spell, except it is instantly cast, and the item wearer doesn't need to use a memorized spell to do so.\nThe spell can be removed by, a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, or a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell as usual.\nThe player will know when the spell effect is expired or removed, because the \"Protection from Normal Missiles\" cylinder graphic will be gone.\nThe item provides has no other abilities."}
