{"id": "56171", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56171", "title": "MINDFL02.ITM", "text": "The MINDFL02 is an equipped item for the &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Illithid\"&gt;Vampiric Illithid&lt;/a&gt; as their only attack weapon. It isn't droppable.\nEffects.\nThe weapon is a magical and enchanted +3 item that has a range of 1 foot and speed factor of 0.\nThe weapon inflicts 1d6+4 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; on each hit and is augmented by the vampiric illithid's &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute, which is +4 damage.\nWhen the weapon scores a hit, it affects the target with a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effect, reducing experience levels by two.\nThe drain effect (whether it actually works on the target or not) heals the illithid's current &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; value by 2d8 points. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes this weapon so that it also does everything written above, plus it causes the \"Devour brain\" effect reducing the target's current &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 5. The effect last one turn, and can't be dispelled."}
{"id": "49215", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49215", "title": "MINDFLAY.ITM", "text": "MINDFLAY.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by Mind Flayers, (typically equipped in the Quick Weapon 1 slot).\nEffects.\nIt is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapon with an &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level of 2. It only deals 1d2 (&lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;crushing&lt;/a&gt;) damage (no &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nHowever, on each successful hit upon any target, five points of &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; are Drained. The attack bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, offers no saving throw, and the effect cannot be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt;. The effect last for 30 seconds, however, successive hits are cumulative. If the target's intelligence is drained to 0 or less, instant death results.\nThe player will know if a character is under the effect in two ways:\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod furnishes the &lt;a href=\"Ulitharid\"&gt;Ulitharids&lt;/a&gt; in the game with a modded melee weapon, that is similar to the MINDFLAY.ITM except it has a reach of 3 feet."}
