{"id": "46104", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46104", "title": "MINHP1.ITM", "text": "MINHP1.ITM is an undroppable item equipped to creatures that the game developers do not want to die immediately (or at all).\nIt is sometimes used to ensure that a creature will not be killed unexpectedly, without having an opportunity to speak their last words or transform into something else. It can also be utilized to make a creature invulnerable to death, regardless of what the player may try - such as the creature &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt; in certain situations.\nEffects.\nThe item grants the following Immunity to effects (and the corresponding Icon/Spell overlays), including the Op Code:\nNatural/Non-magical effects (Numbers in paratheses are &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; designators):\nEffects that are \"Not dispel/Bypass resistance\":"}
{"id": "53705", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53705", "title": "MISTHO.ITM", "text": "MISTHO.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Mist%20Horror\"&gt;Mist Horror&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Swamp%20Horror\"&gt;Swamp Horror&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nThe attack weapon applies a 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; or 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; to the target. Damage type selected based on AC of the target (whichever is most favorable to attacker).\nAn additional 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; is inflicted as well. This is elemental damage that is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell protections.\nThe weapon strikes as a +3 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can strike, but the item is also not flagged as magical.\nEach hit by this item has a 30% probability of exposing the target to a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect and a -10 &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale&lt;/a&gt; modifier lasting 5 rounds. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spells with a -2 penalty will negate. The effects can be blocked by magic resistance but are unaffected by spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. These negative status effects can be dispelled.\nAdditionally, when the weapon makes a successful attack, the target creature has a lighting effect animation played over the creature sprite on any hit. If the target creature is misses the saving throw, then a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; icon will be displayed in the character's portrait for the duration of the effects."}
{"id": "55663", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55663", "title": "MISTICE.ITM", "text": "MISTICE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various creatures such as the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Mist\"&gt;Ice Mist&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; (selected based on target's AC defenses), as well as an additional 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe attack has a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nA successful attack exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect and a -10 &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale&lt;/a&gt; modifier lasting 5 rounds, unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spell is achieved with a -2 penalty. \nThe effect can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; but will bypass &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nRegardless of if the saving throw is made, a hit will play a lighting effect over the target's sprite.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "55665", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55665", "title": "MISTPO.ITM", "text": "MISTPOE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various creatures such as the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Mist\"&gt;Poison Mist&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 1d2 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; as well as an additional 1d10 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe attack has a range of one foot, and speed factor of 1.\nA successful attack exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 5 seconds, unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death is achieved with a -2 penalty. \nIf the saving throw is failed, and the target isn't immune to the Poison status effect or poison damage, then 2 points of damage is incurred each second, for five seconds. Multiple hits are additive to the target. Additionally, the targeted player character/companion will display a \"Poisoned\" icon on their portrait, as well as a text string reference in the combat log reading \"Poisoned\".\nThe effect can't be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and will bypass &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe poisoned condition can't be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nRegardless of if the saving throw is made, a hit will play a lighting effect over the target's sprite.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "53595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53595", "title": "MISTVA.ITM", "text": "MISTVA.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Mist\"&gt;Vampiric Mist&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nThe attack weapon applies a 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; to the target, and the choice is determined by whichever damage type has the most favorable &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; rating for the attacker to overcome. If there are no differences between either type, then crushing damage is applied.\nThe weapon strikes as a +3 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can strike, but the item is also not flagged as magical.\nEach hit on a target will heal the attacker's current HP modifier by +4. Each hit has an 18% probability of &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;level draining&lt;/a&gt; 1 experience level from the target, no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; and no resistance applies.\nAdditionally, when the weapon makes a successful attack, the wielder has a lighting effect animation played over the creature sprite (signifying the healing effect). If the target creature is struck and the level drain effect probability triggers, then a different lighting effect plays over the target creature's sprite (even if they are protected from level drain effects)."}
{"id": "47297", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47297", "title": "MISTVA2.ITM", "text": "This is an NPC only item that grants +3 enchantment attacks. Used by &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Wraith\"&gt;Vampiric Wraith&lt;/a&gt; creature.\nThe weapon is used in melee attacks and on a successful strike inflicts 2d4 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and +10 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;. It cannot be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell protections.\nWhen the weapon strikes a lighting effect plays over the target's sprite (indicating a hit).\nThe magical damage heals the wielder by 4 points, up to the creature's maximum HP.\nThere is a 50% chance that the blow will induce a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effect, reducing the experience level of the target by 1. There is no saving throw. It bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the 50% level drain occurs, the combat log will display a text string reading - \"One Level Drained\"."}
{"id": "53596", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53596", "title": "MISTWA.ITM", "text": "MISTWA.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Wandering%20Horror\"&gt;Wandering Horror&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nThe attack weapon applies a 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; to the target.\nThe weapon strikes as a +3 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can strike, but the item is also not flagged as magical.\nEach hit on a target can apply a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect, but a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spells will negate. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block the stun.\nAdditionally, when the weapon makes a successful attack, the target creature has a lighting effect animation played over the creature sprite (even if the saving throw is made). If the target creature is misses the saving throw, then a text string in the combat log displays \"Stunned\". A \"Stun\" icon will be placed on the target's portrait as well. If the target is protected against stun, then the text message and icon may not be assigned (it all depends on how the immunity effect item or spell is coded)."}
{"id": "49349", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49349", "title": "MONHP1.ITM", "text": "MONHP1.ITM is an undroppable item used primarily by &lt;a href=\"Trolls\"&gt;Trolls&lt;/a&gt; to keep them alive, but unconscious, while they are regenerating.\nEffects.\nIts single natural/non-magical global effect is Minimum HP (Op Code 208) with a value of 1.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, it has no other immunity effects.\nCreatures.\nIt may also be equipped on other creatures the game developers do not want to die. It is sometimes used to ensure that a creature will not be killed unexpectedly, without having an opportunity to speak their last words or transform into something else.\nIt also may be provided to a creature so that hit point death cannot occur so that a script can run and execute, or a creature transformation occurs, or certain items equipped on the creature can be removed or replaced by another, all by an individual creature file script to achieve a plot outcome or gameplay feature."}
{"id": "55661", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55661", "title": "MONHP80.ITM", "text": "MONHP80.ITM is an undroppable item used by a particular non-player creature to ensure its current Hit point limit isn't changed by any condition while the item is equipped. \nThe game engine scripting and creature design can use this item to keep a creature viable until a certain plot condition is met, typically removing the item from the creature at that time.\nEffects.\nIts single natural/non-magical global effect is Minimum HP limit (&lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 208) with a value of 80. \nIn other words, the creature(s) HP value will not drop below the value specified, which is 80 for this item. \nUnlike &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, it has no other immunity effects."}
{"id": "52072", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52072", "title": "MOVE7.ITM", "text": "MOVE7.ITM is an undroppable set of boots equipped by various creatures. For example, the &lt;a href=\"Ulitharid\"&gt;Ulitharid&lt;/a&gt; uses this item.\nThe equipped item sets a flat value modifier to a creature's movement rate, and that value is 7. A default player characters movement rate is 9 for comparison purposes.\nIt has no animation assigned and other effects."}
{"id": "51274", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51274", "title": "MOVRAT10.ITM", "text": "MOVRAT10.ITM is an undroppable item worn in one of a creature's ring slots that simply sets the wearer's movement rate to 10. The default normal movement rate for most creatures in the saga is 9. \nIt has no animation assigned. The item has no other powers or abilities."}
