{"id": "50889", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50889", "title": "MUMMYW.ITM", "text": "MUMMYW.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummy&lt;/a&gt; creatures. It is placed in one of the creature's \"Quick Weapon\" slots.\nIt is considered a non-magical and Unenchanted item and deals 1d12 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; modifier), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 3.\nIt has the ability to inflict a damage dealing &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt; effect on a successful strike on the target.\nThe target must save vs. Death or a disease effect will be applied. The disease lasts for 30 seconds (5 rounds) and applies 1 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; damage per second until the disease expires or is cured. The target's portrait will display a \"Nauseated\" icon (Icon no. 7) while the disease effect runs its course. This effect can't be blocked by magic resistance or spell level protections and cannot be dispelled."}
{"id": "51519", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51519", "title": "Ma Jansen", "text": "Ma Jansen is Jan's mother and can be found inside the ground floor of &lt;a href=\"The%20Jansen%20Home\"&gt;The Jansen Home&lt;/a&gt;. \nWhen Jan first enters the home as part of the &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen%20Summoned%20Home\"&gt;Jan Jansen Summoned Home&lt;/a&gt; quest, Ma Jansen will have some dialogue with her son, and also not be completely happy to see Jan's new companions, the party.\nMa let's Jan know that &lt;a href=\"Lissa\"&gt;Lissa&lt;/a&gt;, upstairs, need to speak with him. Something is up, requiring Jan's attention."}
{"id": "2868", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2868", "title": "Mace", "text": "Maces are like clubs, but they have metal head instead. Maces are held in one hand, but due to weight of 10 lbs, they are slow weapons with a speed factor of 7. Most maces can be wielded by warriors, &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, if they have a &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 10 points. They can inflict 2-7 points of crushing damage. Maces have their own weapon proficiency, except in Baldur's Gate, where it's in blunt weapon proficiency instead. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; and . Maces are sold at most stores which sell weapons in all games."}
{"id": "3828", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3828", "title": "Mace +1", "text": "Mace +1 is an enchanted weapon. Compared to a normal &lt;a href=\"mace\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;, it has speed factor which is one point lower, weighs a bit less, and has +1 bonus to damage and THAC0. Also this weapon can harm enemies immune to normal weapons, because it's enhanced. It falls in the mace proficiency, except in the original &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, where it's in blunt weapons proficiency instead."}
