{"id": "6671", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6671", "title": "Mace of Disruption", "text": "The Mace of Disruption is an enchanted in \"Baldur's Gate II\", that is especially useful against the . The smith &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt; is able to upgrade the original +3 weapon with &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;illithium ore&lt;/a&gt; to a +5 weapon with additional protection against &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;.\nMace of Disruption +1.\nThe weapon's actual enchantment level is +3 regarding what it can strike. The +1 refers to its &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus. The weapon applies 1d6+2 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;. Against creatures it has a doubled damage of 2d6+4 and may destroy them with any successful hit if the undead target creature fails to &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs. death with a penalty of 4.\nMace of Disruption +2.\nThe upgraded version of the mace now strikes as a +5 enchanted weapon against all foes. The +2 in mace's name refers only to the &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus. The mace also has an increased damage bonus to 3. The stats versus undead aren't modified, but the wielder of the weapon will now have immunity against any &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effects.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes Kangaax the Demilich and the &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Demilich (Watcher's Keep)&lt;/a&gt; immune to the &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; effect, such as applied by the Mace of Disruption."}
