{"id": "6278", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6278", "title": "Mae'Var", "text": "Mae'Var is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who is the leader of one of the smaller &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;guildhalls&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Not content with his current station, he is planning to assassinate &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt; so he can rise in rank within the Shadow Thief hierarchy.\nIt is rumored that Mae'Var may have been hired by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Irenicu&lt;/a&gt;s to kidnap &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and that he conspired with the Night Knives of Esmeltaran to snatch the Ward outside the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and bring the prisoner to Amn. \nGameplay.\nOnce hostilities breakout against Mae'Var, he and his fellow guild members will be waiting in the lower level of the guild. By script, he was designed to cast a number of spells, and utilize his fairly high-level mage ability. The creature script is well designed and extensive for the unmodded game. The problem is (developer error?) that he has equipped armor that disables spell casting. So, while it is possible in the game engine coding to force a spell cast by script even if wearing armor, this is actually not the case, and Mae'Var can't cast any of his spells. The info box documents what spells he might have been able to use.\nDuring the events of the \"Shadows of Amn\", Renal Bloodscalp will send you to work under Mae'Var to spy on him and find proof of his suspected treachery. if proof can be found, Renal will most likely want you to dispatch Mae'Var.\nMae'Var has enlisted the thayan mage &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt; to his services - but Gorion's Ward will learn that Edwin is open to betray his new master during the &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Mae'Var Treachery quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nGallery.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to Mae'Var. He is a level 13/15 Mage/Thief with Conjurer Kit. To begin with, he is assigned a new default AI script combining his ability to backstab and spell cast as a mage. If you have the \"Smarter Mages\" component installed this will be included. He gets some different memorized spells to work with as well. Mae'Var also is no longer wearing any equipped torso armor (he still has the invisible &lt;a href=\"HELMNOAN.ITM\"&gt;HELMNOAN.ITM&lt;/a&gt;). This allows SCS to be able to employ its existing spell casting scripts for the Mage/Thief.\nAt the beginning of hostilities, he will employ a spell contingency protecting himself with Improved Invisibility, Non-detection and Spell Deflection. If he is approached by an invisble opponent, the SCS script will show an on-screen text message indicating he has heard something or suspects a spy, and he auto casts an &lt;a href=\"Oracle\"&gt;Oracle&lt;/a&gt; spell. His cohorts and allied Priest of Cyric will also move toward any detected intruders.\nMae'Var also has a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; loaded with a double &lt;a href=\"Color%20Spray\"&gt;Color Spray&lt;/a&gt; attack. If given enough time, the tricky rogue will also be able to get up a PfMW, and cast &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; at a vulnerable party member. In short, the SCS version of Mae'Var is a much more difficult challenge than the unmodded game. Mae'Var and any allied thieves (who turn invisible via potions) will attempt backstab attacks on the party. "}
{"id": "8646", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8646", "title": "Mae'Var's Guildhall", "text": "Mae'Var's Guildhall is a tavern and store in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Docks%20District\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt;. It's primary purpose is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; guildhall run by the thief &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt;. It plays second hand to the main &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thief%20Guildhall\"&gt;Shadow Thief Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;, which is located in the same area and is run by &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nFirst Floor (front half).\nEntering the \"tavern\" you'll meet the humble proprietor of the establishment, &lt;a href=\"Gorch\"&gt;Gorch&lt;/a&gt;. He'll offer to sell you \"things... things sold to me by those in need\". And you can buy a drink if you your thirsty. The rear of the place is off limits. This will change once you have begun the &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt; side quest. The chest has a moderate lock difficulty, but yields a respectable amount of .\nFirst Floor (rear half).\nOnce you have gained access to this area, you'll discover that it's two separate rooms, one with stairs leading up to the second floor and the other with stairs leading down to the basement. The minor loot is easy pickings from the tables and bookshelves.\nSecond Floor.\nA lavish front bedroom, Mae'Var's master bedroom, and a shadow thief training area are found on this floor of the guildhall. Except for Mae'Var's strongbox, which requires a special &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Strongbox%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; to open, all other locked (and trapped) containers on the floor are capable of being defeated by a highly &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;dexterous&lt;/a&gt; thief (the proper potion pick-me-up doesn't hurt either).\nThird Floor.\nHere you'll meet the illustrious companion, &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt;, once you've performed a task for Mae'Var (he won't be here otherwise). He'll play a role in helping to uncover Mae'Var's treachery but of course, Edwin being Edwin, he'll first demand that you perform a task for him too. The floor is comprised of a general purpose room, three dining rooms, and one large bedroom with four beds. Three locked chests, a few tables, and some bookshelves are available to pillage.\nCellar.\nA storage area with a few circular tables, some cells for keeping &lt;a href=\"Kamuzu\"&gt;folks&lt;/a&gt; imprisoned, and a torture area are what you'll find down here. And of course, you'll finally meet Mae'Var, who's busy torturing his cousin &lt;a href=\"Lin\"&gt;Lin&lt;/a&gt;. He's got some protection standing around him too, in case some visitors might decide to become unruly. And like all good thief buildings there's a secret exit with access that leads to the streets. Every table and container, except one, have low grade weapons or other loot to grab. \nOther loot.\n\"Mae'Var's Guildhall\".\nIf you're able to access every container within the guildhall, you'll come away with:\n\"Stronghold\".\nArmor/Weapons:\nMiscellaneous:\nMod content.\nBoth the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mods make a number of changes to the encounters, abilities, scripts and numbers of characters associated with this area and any quests involved in this place. This includes if the area is taken by the PC or Party (with Mods that allow that) as a &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "36220", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36220", "title": "Mae'Var's Letter", "text": "Mae'Var's Letter is a letter from &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; requesting that assassins kill &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt;. This incriminating item is needed in the quest &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt; and can be found in a locked strongbox in Mae'Var's bedroom on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;guildhall&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt; is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Strongbox%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; that's needed to open the container.\nAfter delivering the letter to Renal Bloodscalp and killing Mae'Var, if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; with no other &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;, Bloodscalp will offer the Ward Mae'Var's former position as &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild%20Stronghold\"&gt;head of the thieves' guild&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise, &lt;a href=\"The%20Shadow%27s%20Blade\"&gt;The Shadow's Blade&lt;/a&gt; is the reward."}
{"id": "30301", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30301", "title": "Mae'Var's Strongbox Key", "text": "Mae'Var's Strongbox Key is in &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt;'s inventory in \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\". It is used to complete the sidequest \"&lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt;\" by allowing access to &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt;'s locked chest on the second floor of &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt;.\nEdwin will give the player this key if they progress the sidequest enough. They may also\u00a0kill him for it, but may not &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt; it."}
