{"id": "7371", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7371", "title": "Smaeluv Orcslicer", "text": "Smaeluv Orcslicer is a member of an adventuring party found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nHe wields a &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword%2C%20Cursed%20Berserking\"&gt;cursed two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt; which will make him attack both his allies and enemies. He can be disarmed via &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; and won't reequip the sword afterwards, but, despite that, it still cannot be stolen as it's flagged as \"not stealable\". \nWill attack the closest creature and the effect will cease when hostilities are over, meaning all enemies in the area are no longer enemies or they are dead.\nSmaeluv is found with his fellow band members &lt;a href=\"Mencar%20Pebblecrusher\"&gt;Mencar Pebblecrusher&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Brennan%20Risling\"&gt;Brennan Risling&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Amon\"&gt;Sorcerous Amon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pooky\"&gt;Pooky&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to Smaeluv. He is assigned a default SCS AI script for smarter tactical decision making, including threat recognition and opponent vulnerability assessment - even while \"Berserk\". \nSmaeluv now has 5 pips in two-handed sword weapon proficiency. He also has 2 pips in the two-handed weapon fighting style. This will boost its THAC0, melee damage and get his &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; to 4. The weapon fighting style gives an extra damage, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, and will now &lt;a href=\"Critical%20hit\"&gt;Critical hit&lt;/a&gt; more often. A random SCS treasure is added to his inventory. "}
{"id": "2809", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2809", "title": "Small Shield", "text": "Small Shields are lightweight shields with significantly more surface area than &lt;a href=\"buckler\"&gt;buckler&lt;/a&gt;s, allowing for better protection against physical attacks. However, neither of these two smallest shields protect against missiles. Small shields have a weight of 3 lbs and it requires 4 &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield them.\nThe shields are available in three colors. The BG1 versions are round wooden shields with metal padding, whereas the BG2 versions have the shape a Wedge, with additional indents at half height."}
