{"id": "11297", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11297", "title": "Small Spider", "text": "Small Spiders, while still much larger than the common house spider, are smaller than the average spider encountered throughout the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;game&lt;/a&gt;. Beyond their unusual size, about that of a large dog, they have no remarkable traits except that, unlike most , small spiders are unable to &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; a target creature with a successful hit. However they are still immune to &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, but can be affected by other immobilizing spells such as &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe two small spider creatures detailed on this page have their allegiance listed as neutral, but they instantly become enemies upon sight of any party member."}
