{"id": "5970", "revid": "283964", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5970", "title": "Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District", "text": "Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District questline can be introduced as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; - simply by entering the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; for the first time.\nAquisition.\n&lt;a href=\"Lieutenant%20Aegisfield\"&gt;Lieutenant Aegisfield&lt;/a&gt; is located in the north end of the district and will initiate conversation with the party. They'll hear about a series of grisly murders - and victims whose skin has been removed. The party may ask questions and make remarks about this information. Further on, various townsfolk are concerned and disgusted by the remains of murdered victims still laying in the street. Who's going to clean up this mess?\nAbbreviated walkthrough.\nAegisfield confronts the tanner.\nIf you choose to report your findings to Aegisfield, he will confront the tanner to confirm your story. Some party members may comment on how he may not have the ability to deal with this alone, and you will probably get the feeling that this isn't finished.\nFollowing up.\nCompleting this quest, regardless of which method is used, will trigger two unmarked quests. The first is &lt;a href=\"Helping%20Tiris%20in%20Trademeet\"&gt;Helping Tiris in Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;. The second, which the player is guided towards by reading the &lt;a href=\"Tanner%27s%20Letter\"&gt;Tanner's Letter&lt;/a&gt;, is &lt;a href=\"Find%20Rejiek%27s%20ally\"&gt;Find Rejiek's ally&lt;/a&gt; - this second quest leads to the marked quest &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Ooze%27s%20Lounge\"&gt;Ooze's Lounge&lt;/a&gt; Mod requires a key in order to open a Slum District Sewer Grate. You will find it somewhere in the Tanner's Shop if you look and explore adequately.\nGallery.\nPeople involved: \"Portraits from &lt;a href=\"Portraits%20Portraits%20Everywhere\"&gt;Portraits Portraits Everywhere&lt;/a&gt;\""}
