{"id": "51181", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51181", "title": "Sorcerous Amin", "text": "Sorcerous Amin can be found within the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt;. This wizard functions as one of the Baron's guards.\nAs a battle begins, this mage can actually be disrupted before being able to initiate any protective spells. The wizard will attempt to apply a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Invocation&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;. Whether successful or not the mage will then attempt to try a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. After that offensive or disabling spells will be selected on observed targets, such as &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Silence\"&gt;Power Word, Silence&lt;/a&gt; at clerics or Mages in the party. A &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; is aimed at a party member who has a Spell turning protection. &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; is cast as well. A &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt; is likely attempted, and then various disabling and damage dealing spells. The wizard can attempt an additional stoneskin if the first is removed, consumed or breached.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default SCS \"Smarter Mage\" script for threat and vulnerability assessed spell casting behavior. Amin is now a level 14 Conjurer. The mage will launch a series of uninterruptible self-buffs upon commencement of hostilities. These include &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Divination&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;.\nNow cloaked in invisibility, the mage will attempt to conjure an &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt; to smash the party. Then the mage will utilize its advanced script to conduct opponent vulnerability assessments to determine what appropriate spells are best to harm the party or counter party protections on observed targets in range. This could include another self-buff such as &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;, or a Spell sequencer. The mage has a contingency of &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; which will automatically fire if certain threat conditions present, as well as another stoneskin if breached or the initial one is removed/consumed. \nA variety of spell protection and combat removal options are possible using &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;. As a conjurer, the mage favors summoned creatures as its best attack option, attempting to bring forth various elementals and monsters. The mage also has some quick casting &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Silence\"&gt;Power Word, Silence&lt;/a&gt; to shut down an unprotected Cleric or Mage. The mage has the following prepared for instant use:\nThe wizard has one pip weapon proficiency in quarterstaff and dart. Additional SCS Random treasures are placed in the inventory"}
{"id": "7375", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7375", "title": "Sorcerous Amon", "text": "Sorcerous Amon is a member of an adventuring party that's found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt;. His familiar is the &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imp&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pooky\"&gt;Pooky&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSorceros Amon is a spell casting mage with several offensive damage spells as well as using invisibility if a fight breaks out. \nAt the outset, if able, Amon will open with a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; to self-protect. \nThe mage will then look for visible targets in order to launch offensive damage dealing spells such as &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs the battle progresses a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; and or &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt; can be cast as well.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to the creature. Amon is now a Level 10 &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Specialist Mage&lt;/a&gt; with an Conjurer Kit. It is assigned an SCS \"Smarter Mage\" AI, for better threat recognition for defensive purposes, and will see creatures who are vulnerable to its spell casts. It will not waste spells upon immune enemies, but instead seek another target, or try and remove the defenses first. A new memorized arsenal of spells is provided, with a lean towards Conjuration and Summoning options. With SCS installed, Amon will summon creatures several times to assist in battle. The longer he remains active, the more creature summoning will occur. \nAmon will initiate an instant buff with &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. It will then go on the offensive.\nAmon has a prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; readied with double &lt;a href=\"Color%20Spray\"&gt;Color Spray&lt;/a&gt;, which he will use if able.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed Amon's spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "3481", "revid": "46918295", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3481", "title": "Sorcerous Sundries", "text": "Sorcerous Sundries is a colorful circular building located in the district of &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; within the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Its primary function is the selling and buying of magical weapons and armor, projectiles and ammunition, spell scrolls, wands and potions. Non-magical weapons and armor, along with random miscellaneous items, will also be purchased for resale.\nFirst Floor.\nAs soon as the party walks in the door, the owner, a mage named &lt;a href=\"Halbazzer%20Drin\"&gt;Halbazzer Drin&lt;/a&gt;, is observed standing behind the counter and &lt;a href=\"Ordulinian\"&gt;Ordulinian&lt;/a&gt; is standing in front of it. Ordulinian will give you a quest should you speak with him.\nSecond Floor.\nChapter Five.\nOn the second floor, a mage named &lt;a href=\"Niemain\"&gt;Niemain&lt;/a&gt; is practicing a new spell and will attack, along with fellow mages &lt;a href=\"Oulam\"&gt;Oulam&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wheber%20Ott\"&gt;Wheber Ott&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"William%20Garst\"&gt;William Garst&lt;/a&gt;, if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; or any other member of the party annoys him. Should this happen, disposing of the attackers will not lead to any sort of repercussions.\nEntering with &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; in your party will cause\u00a0Niemain to initiate unique dialog with you, mentioning that Xzar had made frequent reports about you and your activities fighting the Iron Throne. If you ask them who they are, Niemain will reveal himself to be Xzar's superior and a member of the Zhentarim. He will advise you to search the Iron Throne tower in the West of the city, as they are a mutual enemy.\nThe exchange is slightly different if &lt;a href=\"Montaron\"&gt;Montaron&lt;/a&gt; is in your party, but Xzar is dead - he will point you towards the Iron Throne headquarters, but will not reveal any more information as he does not trust you and does not value Montaron as particularly capable without Xzar.\nEither way, Niemain and his group will then leave without a fight.\nChapter Seven.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Chapter%207\"&gt;Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; which serves as the prologue for the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt; campaign, Gorion's Ward is requested to fetch some items for Halbazzer as part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Sorcerous%20Sundries%20Caper\"&gt;The Sorcerous Sundries Caper&lt;/a&gt; side quest.\u00a0\nOn the second floor the party will interrupt a motley crew of thieves, led by a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Sethyl\"&gt;Sethyl&lt;/a&gt;, who are attempting to conduct a robbery.\nThe surrounding cupboards become active containers and can be looted for a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Shielding\"&gt;Potion of Magic Shielding&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Resistance\"&gt;Potion of Fire Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. The nearby shelves contain scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Electricity\"&gt;Protection From Electricity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Cold\"&gt;Protection From Cold&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Petrification\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Petrification&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52144", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52144", "title": "Sorcerous Sundries (SoD)", "text": "Sorcerous Sundries is a colorful circular building located in the district of &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; within the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Its primary function is the selling and buying of magical weapons and armor, projectiles and ammunition, spell scrolls, wands and potions. Non-magical weapons and armor, along with random miscellaneous items, will also be purchased for resale.\nFirst Floor.\nAs soon as the party walks in the door, the owner, a mage named &lt;a href=\"Halbazzer%20Drin\"&gt;Halbazzer Drin&lt;/a&gt;, is observed standing behind the counter and his cousin &lt;a href=\"Kazzrem\"&gt;Kazzrem&lt;/a&gt; is standing on the central steps. Both are willing to sell a separate selection of items.\nSecond Floor.\nDuring the prologue for the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt; campaign, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is requested to fetch some items for Halbazzer as part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Sorcerous%20Sundries%20Caper\"&gt;The Sorcerous Sundries Caper&lt;/a&gt; side quest.\u00a0\nOn the second floor the party will interrupt a motley crew of thieves, led by a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Sethyl\"&gt;Sethyl&lt;/a&gt;, who are attempting to conduct a robbery.\nThe surrounding cupboards become active containers and can be looted for a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Shielding\"&gt;Potion of Magic Shielding&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Resistance\"&gt;Potion of Fire Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;. The nearby shelves contain scrolls of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Electricity\"&gt;Protection From Electricity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Cold\"&gt;Protection From Cold&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Petrification\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Petrification&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "12713", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12713", "title": "Sorrel", "text": "Sorrel is a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Mercenary%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; who is found standing in the shadows of the &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;. He will tell you how the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; organization has been taken over by &lt;a href=\"Angelo%20Dosan\"&gt;Angelo&lt;/a&gt;, now that &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt; is dead, and how Angelo has been abusing his new power. He will also mention that, despite Angelo's power grab, some Flaming Fist members are still loyal to &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;\nWhich results in the following &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry:"}
{"id": "15060", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15060", "title": "Sorrem", "text": "Sorrem is involved in &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad's&lt;/a&gt; side quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20and%20Stars\"&gt;Blade and Stars&lt;/a&gt;. Upon confronting him, following a recent attack of the party by several &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon%20Monk\"&gt;Dark Moon Monk's&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, he can either be allowed to lead the party to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; cult's safe house in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; or killed when he turns hostile. He carries a &lt;a href=\"Sorrem%27s%20Note\"&gt;note&lt;/a&gt; that, when read, reveals the location of the &lt;a href=\"Cloud%20Peaks\"&gt;Cloud Peaks&lt;/a&gt; area on your &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;. This is where the cult's newest temple has recently been established. You can pickpocket the note, which will also reveal the location. If you do, Sorrem will have nothing to say to you.\nSorrem has been promised admission into the order if he leads the Dark Moon cult to Rasaad.\nDialogue.\n\"Who do you think you are, bustin' in on me like this?\"\nThis starts a cut scene where Sorrem meets the party at the safe house.\n\"All right, here's the place, just like I promised. Since you've been so good about not killing me, I brought you a present: the key to this building.\"\nHe then heads inside the house. Once inside he addresses the party once more.\n\"In fact, tonight's all about my bringin' presents for my best pals. Hey, boys! Here are those friends I told you about. Come on out an' say hello.\"\nAnd with that both Sorrem and the Lieutenant head upstairs while four Dark Moon Monk's appear from the nearby rooms and attack."}
{"id": "30858", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30858", "title": "Sorrem's Note", "text": "Sorrem's Note is a &lt;a href=\"scroll\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; found on &lt;a href=\"Sorrem\"&gt;Sorrem&lt;/a&gt; after he has been killed during &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt; side quest. It is the second of three notes that detail the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Moon\"&gt;Dark Moon&lt;/a&gt; cult's plot to have &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt; killed. This note provides the emphasis for Sorrem to complete his task and receive his reward.\nWhen the note is added to your inventory, the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; will be updated with the location of the Dark Moon cult's temple in the Cloud Peaks mountains."}
{"id": "48778", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48778", "title": "Sorsha", "text": "Sorsha is &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;-assassin hired by an anti-magic faction in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. She only appears in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; during the final phase of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nSorsha is accompanied by six others, including four fighter-assassins named &lt;a href=\"Sergeant%20Natula\"&gt;Sergeant Natula&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tyrian\"&gt;Tyrian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vilhelm\"&gt;Vilhelm&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Jalin%20Tix\"&gt;Jalin Tix&lt;/a&gt;, along with &lt;a href=\"Mahar\"&gt;Mahar&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;), and &lt;a href=\"Alnarow\"&gt;Alnarow&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;).\nAt the beginning of combat, Sorsha casts Bark Skin, Bless and Animal Summoning II. If the animals are killed she can follow up with Call Woodland Beings. Invisibility Purge and Charm Person or Mammal are also possibilities. She might also cast Flame Blade before closing to melee. If brought near death, she can cast Cure Serious Wounds and Heal."}
{"id": "7926", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7926", "title": "Soul Reaver", "text": "Soul Reaver is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt; +4 that can only be wielded by &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;neutral and evil-aligned&lt;/a&gt; warriors and &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s. \nGameplay.\nEach hit on a target applies a cumulative 2-point penalty to their &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, lasting 20 rounds. The effect cannot be removed."}
