{"id": "4024", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4024", "title": "Soultaker Dagger", "text": "The Soultaker Dagger was used by &lt;a href=\"Durlag%20Trollkiller\"&gt;Durlag Trollkiller&lt;/a&gt; to capture the soul of a powerful demon named &lt;a href=\"Aec%27Letec\"&gt;Aec'Letec&lt;/a&gt; many years ago. It is a normal 1D4 &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; and it has no magical enhancements.\nThe first time you enter the &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hurgan%20Stoneblade\"&gt;Hurgan Stoneblade&lt;/a&gt; will approach you and request that you retrieve it for him from &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. The dagger is in the possession of the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Knight\"&gt;Demon Knight&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in his chamber room located on the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Four%29\"&gt;fourth labyrinth level&lt;/a&gt; beneath the tower.\nWhen the dagger is brought back to &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;, the party will immediately have an encounter with of a unnamed cult. Regardless of the outcome, the members of this cult will gain possession of the dagger and use it to revive Aec'Letec, whom you'll have to kill.\nNote.\nAt the end of the campaign, a &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;hooded man&lt;/a&gt;, using this dagger, murdered of yours and trapping the victim's soul within it. If the dagger is in your inventory before the scene, it will be removed from your bags. It also appears in a cinematic later in the game."}
{"id": "4309", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4309", "title": "South Baldur's Gate", "text": "South Baldur's Gate is one of nine districts of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate city&lt;/a&gt;. The harbor in the center partially separates the buildings into east and west, but the party can move throught the area without traveling to different districts.\nAssassination.\nThe five &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt;s in what looks to be a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1201\"&gt;restaurant&lt;/a&gt;, are not noted as an assassination attempt by other walkthroughs, because they do not happen at a public location. Nonetheless, they follow the same pattern as all other assassins when the lead Ogre Mage makes it clear that they are agents of the Iron Throne, intent on killing &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; specifically. They give altogether, and have some high value random loot. It is wise to guard yourself against mind tricks, specifically &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt;.\nReputation Trap.\nIf your Reputation is lower than 3 you will be attacked by a group of three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMPUN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Scout\"&gt;Flaming Fist Scout&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Battle%20Wizard\"&gt;Flaming Fist Battle Wizard&lt;/a&gt;. This group of soldiers will attack suddenly on the streets.\nCity map overview.\n City grid you are at the X:\n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NW&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NE&lt;/a&gt; \n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;E&lt;/a&gt; \n o|X|o &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;SW&lt;/a&gt;|S|&lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;SE&lt;/a&gt;"}
