{"id": "31664", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31664", "title": "Southern Baldur's Gate", "text": ""}
{"id": "22668", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22668", "title": "Southern Dungeons", "text": "The Southern Dungeons is a crypt containing tombs and can be accessed via the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; beneath the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nGameplay and walkthrough.\nMosaic Hall.\nEntering from the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; puts you in the northwest part of a large hall with an ornate tile mosaic face on the floor. Checking will reveal traps in each eye, the chin, and left hand (crossed over to the right side). However, walking pass the crest/crown of the face to disarm traps, sets off a silent trigger that crosses the entire hall. Be prepared for undead that spawn, entering in from alcoves on either side. Undead include two &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;ghasts&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"Wight\"&gt;wights&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warriors&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"Zombie\"&gt;Zombie&lt;/a&gt; that are immune to normal missiles, and an unamed &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;; the latter, from the northeastern-most alcove that you can be defeated by itself if you don't cross the whole hall while battling the other undead. An urn in the middle of the north wall can be looted.\nA secret door in the southwestern-most alcove leads to hallways to the rest of the dungeon.\nHallways.\nPass the secret door are two &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;mummies&lt;/a&gt;. At the hallway intersection is a group of &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Wraith\"&gt;Wraiths&lt;/a&gt; , and a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Fiend\"&gt;Shadow Fiend&lt;/a&gt;. An urn behind a brazier can be looted.\nTaking the hallway to the southeast you see a standing sarcophagus on the north wall. A trap crosses the hall in front of the sarcophagus. Once disarmed click on the sarcophagus to get a status message \"You may open this sarcophagus if you wish.\" Clicking again releases its occupant which attacks you straight-away.\"An undead thing pulls itself from the sarcophagus, mumbling angry words in some alien tongue. The thing turns its dead eyes towards you as you recoil in horror.\"It is another &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;skeleton warrior&lt;/a&gt;, this one wielding &lt;a href=\"Halcyon\"&gt;Halcyon&lt;/a&gt;, a spear +1 that inflicts an extra point of electrical damage. Pass the sarcophagus is yet another mummy, and beyond it is another group of undead that can respawn later; it includes Mummies and &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghasts&lt;/a&gt; . The hall ends at a small square tomb.\nSouth from the hallway intersection is another trap, to the right of another standing sarcophagus, just north of an alcove. Once disarmed, go just pass the alcove to check again for traps. Disarm the trap just before the brazier, then follow the hall to the southeast to another tomb.\nTombs.\nThe southeast hallway leads to a small room with a square structure. Clicking it reveals, \"This standing sarcophagus is long-sealed by stone.\" Only the urn and crate can be looted.\nThe hallway south leads to a large tomb room. Check the containers here off to the side, however looters have already raided the tomb. \"This tomb has been cracked open and anything of value has been removed. Looters have broken the fingers of the corpse, no doubt to take something it was holding.\"\nNevaziah.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Edwin\"&gt;Edwin's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest to &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20Nether%20Scroll%20for%20Edwin\"&gt;Find the Nether Scroll for Edwin&lt;/a&gt;, you will also have a run-in with &lt;a href=\"Nevaziah\"&gt;Nevaziah&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0 who holds what Edwin seeks; the Nether Scroll.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises undead creatures, the &lt;a href=\"Vampyre%20%28Vampire%20Sub-type%29\"&gt;Vampyre&lt;/a&gt; and Nevaziah with improved AI scripts in this dungeon."}
{"id": "51451", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51451", "title": "Southern Edge", "text": "Southern Edge is a mod for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt; that adds a new district to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;: A shanty settlement just outside the southern city wall.\nIt is part of Lava Del'Vortel's \"Athkatlan Grounds\" mod series.\nOverview.\nThe Southern Edge district has an inn, temple, shops, and various inhabitants.\nThe mod also adds a whole bunch of side-quests that start in the Southern Edge district, or lead you there. Most can be resolved without fighting, making this district suitable as an early-game quest hub.\nHow to start the quests.\nQuests that start in the Southern Edge district:\nQuests that start in other districts, but lead you to the Southern Edge:\nSimilar mods.\nThis mod is part of Lava Del'Vortel's \"Athkatlan Grounds\" series, which also includes these mods:\nOther mods that add new &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; districts include &lt;a href=\"Fishing%20for%20Trouble\"&gt;Fishing for Trouble&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Region%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Region of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "27600", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27600", "title": "Southern dungeons", "text": ""}
{"id": "5220", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5220", "title": "Southwest Baldur's Gate", "text": "Southwest Baldur's Gate is one of nine districts of the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. This area is inhabited by a mix of common and rich townsfolk.\nBuildings.\n&lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Flaming Fist HQ is the biggest building in the district and the following NPCs can be found in or near it.\n&lt;a href=\"Ye%20Olde%20Inn\"&gt;Ye Olde Inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe white building next to the Flaming Fist HQ is the Ye Olde Inn. The inn has a slime problem and the &lt;a href=\"Bartender\"&gt;Bartender&lt;/a&gt; dies a violent death, so no room or drinks here.\n&lt;a href=\"Seven%20Suns\"&gt;Seven Suns&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe large, rectangular, brown-colored building in front of the Ye Olde Inn is the Seven Suns compound. Scar will ask you to investigate the strange goings-on within the trading coster.\n&lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Estate\"&gt;Merchants' League Estate&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe other large rectangular building with the flat roof is the Merchants' League Estate. This building is not accessible if you killed &lt;a href=\"Aldeth%20Sashenstar\"&gt;Aldeth Sashenstar&lt;/a&gt;, a member of the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League\"&gt;Merchants' League&lt;/a&gt;, in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Lodge\"&gt;Cloakwood Lodge&lt;/a&gt; area. However, if you helped Aldeth instead, he'll be waiting outside the building and offer you a quest to help him figure out what's up with his business partners. This will allow the party to get inside and the reward for his quest is a magic sword, 100 gold, possibilities of help later, and a lot of XP.\n&lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Tavern and Inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne of the three buildings in the southwest corner of the district is a generic tavern. Here is where you can find drinks and beds in all four room types. It is also the place to find &lt;a href=\"Phandalyn\"&gt;Phandalyn&lt;/a&gt;, an overzealous &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; who will attack any party that enters whilst containing even one member with an Evil &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;. Killing him in self defense will cause the party to lose &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;; the amount lost scales with current Reputation.\n&lt;a href=\"Sunin%27s%20Home\"&gt;Sunin's Home&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe central building of the three in the southwest corner of the district (the one with the bluish-green tiled roof) is the home of the mage &lt;a href=\"Sunin\"&gt;Sunin&lt;/a&gt; who doesn't like intruders. He will drop a &lt;a href=\"Evermemory\"&gt;Ring of Wizardry&lt;/a&gt;, if he is killed.\nGeneral Stores.\nThere are three general stores within the district. The &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1116%29\"&gt;first&lt;/a&gt; is the red building located behind the Seven Suns compound, across from the Ye Olde Inn. The &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1117%29\"&gt;second&lt;/a&gt; is the red building behind the Merchants' League Estate. The &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1112%29\"&gt;third&lt;/a&gt; one is in the southwest corner next to Sunin's Home.\nMost of what is offered are basic &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, with only a few &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; ones among them. Of note would be a &lt;a href=\"katana\"&gt;katana&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"wakizashi\"&gt;wakizashi&lt;/a&gt;, one &lt;a href=\"Destroyer%20of%20the%20Hills\"&gt;Destroyer of the Hills&lt;/a&gt; and twenty-five &lt;a href=\"arrows%20of%20piercing\"&gt;arrows of piercing&lt;/a&gt; in the \"\" \u2013 while five &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield%20%2B1\"&gt;large shields +1&lt;/a&gt; are available in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", together with several &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1117%29\"&gt;one&lt;/a&gt; of the three shops.\nAll these demand one and a half of the regular value, while they are paying only the half when selling items there. At least two of them offer &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;identification&lt;/a&gt; of any magical item.\n&lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;Potion Shop&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Potion Shop is the blue building located both behind the Seven Suns compound and the first general store.\n&lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Generic Homes&lt;/a&gt;.\nClustered together in the central part of the district and located just south of the Flaming Fist Headquarters are four generic houses. In the biggest of the four, which has bluish-colored roof, you will find &lt;a href=\"Wiven\"&gt;Wiven&lt;/a&gt; and potentially three other members of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;.\nReputation Trap.\nIf your Reputation is lower than 3 you will be attacked by a group of three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMPUN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Scout\"&gt;Flaming Fist Scout&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Battle%20Wizard\"&gt;Flaming Fist Battle Wizard&lt;/a&gt;. This group of soldiers will attack suddenly both on the streets and in the Flaming Fist Headquarters.\nTransitions.\nYou can reach the small portion of the southwestern part of &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; via this area, but the rest of West Baldur's Gate can't be reached from this area.\nCity map overview.\n City grid you are at the X:\n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NW&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NE&lt;/a&gt; \n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;E&lt;/a&gt; \n X|o|o SW|&lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;SE&lt;/a&gt;"}
