{"id": "7974", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7974", "title": "Spectral Brand", "text": "Spectral Brand +4 can acquired when the party accepts &lt;a href=\"The%20Gambling%20Cambion\"&gt;The Gambling Cambion&lt;/a&gt; questline as part of the exploration of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item appears in and .\nGameplay.\nThis weapon is \"missable\", in that the party could refuse to accept the quest needed to obtain it, or the card game during the quest is lost by the party member, and therefore fails to win the blade.\nIf the blade is won (see the screenshot in the gallery below), then an experience reward is also bestowed to each party member.\nThe blade is a +4 enchanted scimitar, which inflicts 1d8+4 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and 1d4 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; on every successful hit.\nThe weapon also bestows a 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus. The weapon weighs 2 lbs. and it has a speed factor of 1. This weapon requires a Strength of 8 to wield.\nOnce per day, the wielder can order the blade to \"dance\", lasting 4 rounds, and the controlled sword leaps out of the user's hand and can fight on its own in similar fashion as a &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword (creature)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player can control the blade and issue its movement and targeting instructions.\nAfter a standard rest period (8-hours), the ability recharges and can be used again.\nThis weapon can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;, which requires the &lt;a href=\"Skull%20of%20the%20Lich\"&gt;Skull of the Lich&lt;/a&gt; and some gold.\nUpgraded.\nSpectral Brand +5 now deals 1d8+5 points of damage and 1d6 points of cold damage and has 5-point THAC0 bonus. \nThe weapon has two new abilities as well:\nNotes.\nThe Armor Piercing Strike could be used in combination with a wielder who can use &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind\"&gt;Whirlwind&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Whirlwind\"&gt;Greater Whirlwind&lt;/a&gt; to do a lot of accurate attacks in a short amount of time. This weapon is a very powerful weapon for druids and perhaps a very good weapon for bards and warriors as well.\nThe Armor Piercing Strike bonus applies to any weapon the character uses while the ability is in effect, e.g.: a thrown dagger, an offhand weapon, a main hand weapon etc."}
