{"id": "49227", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49227", "title": "Spectral Harpist", "text": "A Spectral Harpist is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; spirit of a &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; of \"..the past that guards the present. We harp as specters that others would find rest here.\" Three spectral harpists can be found on the second floor of &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSpectral Harpist are immune to non-magical weapons and &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, have 100% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;electricity&lt;/a&gt;, and 44% &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to immunity to many other effects and spells (see InfoBox, right).\nTheir melee attack does .\nAs undead Harpers they also have an innate ability called &lt;a href=\"Deathsong\"&gt;Deathsong&lt;/a&gt; which causes &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale failure&lt;/a&gt; in enemy targets, leading to &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; for 60 seconds. It also grants the harpist 100% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a +8 bonus to melee damage for 36 seconds."}
{"id": "40595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40595", "title": "Spectral Troll", "text": "A Spectral Troll is a race of &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; that is similar to, but not to be mistaken for, a &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Troll\"&gt;Spirit Troll&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike most trolls, these varieties are highly intelligent. They have a faded or semi-transparent appearance, shifting and ill-defined at the edges of their lanky frame. As such, the giant humanoids are difficult to hit with weaponry and missile fire. In the game, the creatures are not classified as undead, as they are in the 2nd edition Dungeons and Dragons lore.\nThese creatures strike with long sinewy limbs and sharp piercing claws that hit as +3 enchanted items, and inflict 2d6 &lt;a href=\"piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;, which are also modified by their above average strength.\nDue to their spectral ties, these trolls require magical weapons in order to strike them. \nSpectral Trolls have a movement modifier that boosts their walking gait to above that of a normal human by a little more than 20%.\nLike a normal troll, they regenerate damage at 1 &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; per second. Upon being reduced to 1 hit point they are rendered unconscious, there is a brief span of time to permanently kill the creature by means of fire or acid damage, otherwise they rapidly regenerate and rise to fight again.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default AI to the troll for better targeting, threat assessment capability and smarter tactical behavior. \nSeveral Spectral Trolls are added to the exterior and interior of the de'Arnise Keep as part of the Tactical Challenges for BG2 \"Tougher de'Arnise Keep\" component."}
