{"id": "3446", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3446", "title": "Spider's Bane", "text": "Spider's Bane (Spider's Bane +2 in-game) is a magical and enchanted &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt;. Despite what its name may suggest, it does not have any specific attack bonuses against\u00a0&lt;a href=\"spiders\"&gt;spiders&lt;/a&gt;. It bestows the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28status%20effect%29\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt;, granting the wielder immunity against magic and other effects which affect movement like &lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;slow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person\"&gt;hold&lt;/a&gt; and spider webs. It also has the unfortunate side-effect of preventing increases to movement speed as well, such as with &lt;a href=\"The%20Paws%20of%20the%20Cheetah\"&gt;The Paws of the Cheetah&lt;/a&gt; boots, and the character will not gain any benefits from &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;. Like all +2 weapons, it also has +2 bonus to damage and &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and a speed factor two points lower than a normal two-handed sword.\nMod related.\nThough being still present in the game code of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt; does make no appearance in the original campaigns. The \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business&lt;/a&gt;\" implements it with the &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Pai%27Na%20and%20Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Pai'Na and Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
