{"id": "36617", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36617", "title": "Spider Cave", "text": "The Spider Lair is in \"\".\nIt is a small cave located at the base of the mountain in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;. As its name suggests, it is home to a number of monstrous spiders, as well as several &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;-effect traps. If &lt;a href=\"M%27Khiin%20Grubdoubler\"&gt;M'Khiin&lt;/a&gt; is with the party, she will comment about being bothered by all the moans from the dead spirits.\nLayout.\nAlong the walls are several un-highlighted spots that when hovered over will show the \"hand holding a ring\" icon that will produce &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Silk\"&gt;Spider Silk&lt;/a&gt; when interacted with and the &lt;a href=\"Seven-Legged%20Spider\"&gt;Seven-Legged Spider&lt;/a&gt; will drop &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider%20Leg\"&gt;Giant Spider Leg&lt;/a&gt; once killed.\nThe first chamber off the main path has a horde of various spiders, a Web-type trap, and at the back, a wall crack with &lt;a href=\"Severance%20%2B2\"&gt;Severance +2&lt;/a&gt; and several gems.\nIn a chamber, to the northeast is a dead goblin with &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Hide%20Armor%20%2B2\"&gt;Goblin Hide Armor +2&lt;/a&gt;, which will trigger another conversation from M'Khiin.\nAfter killing all the spiders and entering the west-most chamber, the quest/event &lt;a href=\"Beetles%20and%20Spiders\"&gt;Beetles and Spiders&lt;/a&gt; will begin.\nStrategy.\nThe large number of spiders, and corresponding poison, potentially necessitates the use of a large number of &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Poison\"&gt;Slow Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Neutralize%20Poison\"&gt;Neutralize Poison&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt; potions.\nNotes.\nThe four &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Silk\"&gt;Spider Silk&lt;/a&gt;s needed for the &lt;a href=\"Anniversary%20Gift\"&gt;Anniversary Gift&lt;/a&gt; quest that &lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt; will give the player in Chapter 10 are difficult to detect. To collect them, you'll need to move the cursor over the webs on the walls, and in four places the cursor will change to indicate that there's an item to loot. The lootable webs won't glow when pressing the highlight key, making them very hard to acquire. It may be easier to simply wait until you reach chapter 10 and can loot the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Cellar\"&gt;Hidden Cellar&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Man%27s%20Pass\"&gt;Dead Man's Pass&lt;/a&gt;."}
