{"id": "46946", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46946", "title": "Spider Nest", "text": "The Spider Nest is the home of &lt;a href=\"Centeol\"&gt;Centeol&lt;/a&gt; and it is located in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Nest\"&gt;Cloakwood Nest&lt;/a&gt; area. Besides Centeol, there are two of each of the following enemies: &lt;a href=\"Ettercap\"&gt;Ettercap&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword Spider&lt;/a&gt;s. All dialogue options lead to fighting and Centeol will call forth two more giant spiders to join the battle.\nThe treasure trove found near Centeol contains a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Opal%20Ring\"&gt;Fire Opal Ring&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt; , the &lt;a href=\"Discipliner\"&gt;Discipliner&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chelak%27s%20Body\"&gt;Chelak's Body&lt;/a&gt; and the two-handed sword &lt;a href=\"Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuest.\n&lt;a href=\"Spiders%20in%20the%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Spiders in the Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nHelp &lt;a href=\"Tiber\"&gt;Tiber&lt;/a&gt; find his missing brother."}
{"id": "34279", "revid": "272536", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34279", "title": "Spider Silk", "text": "Spider Silk is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThey can be gathered from the walls of the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Lair\"&gt;Spider Lair&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Cellar\"&gt;Hidden Cellar&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Man%27s%20Pass\"&gt;Dead Man's Pass&lt;/a&gt;. On the walls will be patches of spider web that will not be highlighted, but will have the \"hand holding a ring\" icon when moused over. Interacting with them will produce the silk.\nFunction.\n&lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt; requests the item for the &lt;a href=\"Anniversary%20Gift\"&gt;Anniversary Gift&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nTrivia.\nFor unknown reasons, like &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider%20Leg\"&gt;Giant Spider Leg&lt;/a&gt;, this item cannot be placed in a &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt;. Can use the program Near Infinity to change the category from spider bodies to miscellaneous to allow placing in bags of holding."}
{"id": "5907", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5907", "title": "Spider Spawn", "text": "The Spider Spawn spell enables a wizard to conjure forth a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword&lt;/a&gt; spider and obey telepathic commands. \nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a point on the area map where the spider spawn shall appear - and uses the targeting cursor to select the point.\nWhen the spell casting is complete, a monster summoning animation renders at the selected point, and after a few seconds, the spider(s) appear, as \"green circled\" controlled summoned creatures.\nThe summoned spider(s) will act on their own and attack any detected enemies but can also be directed to a particular foe by the caster.\nA spawned spider cannot clear the \"Fog of War' on an unexplored area map.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt; will dimension door itself adjacent to enemy, rather than scramble on its legs toward the enemy.\nSpider spawns are instantly killed by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or if exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpawned spiders cannot transition with the party to a different area map and will remain on the map where they were spawned.\nA spider killed in combat leaves a corpse behind on the map.\nWhen the spell's duration expires, a living spider spawn will disappear from the area map.\nThis spell is often used in conjunction with a &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; spell, as the spiders can move freely within the sticky strands.\nAs a summoned creature, each spider counts toward the summoning cap limit.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset has no direct equivalent to the \"Spider Spawn\" 4th-level Wizard spell. See the External links for the nearest equivalent spell.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod removes the \"Spider Spawn\" spell from the game, including scrolls. The spell is replaced with the following:&lt;br&gt;\nMonster Summoning IV&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 4&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Conjuration&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Medium&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 3 turns&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 1 round&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: Special&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: None&lt;br&gt;\nBy means of this spell, the caster summons a number of monsters, which serve the mage under any conditions. The type and number of creatures that appear depend upon the level of the wizard casting the spell. The summoned creatures will remain under the wizard\u2019s control until they are slain, or the spell duration expires.&lt;br&gt;\n7th : 2 giant spiders&lt;br&gt;\n9th : 3 giant spiders&lt;br&gt;\n12th+ : 3 giant spiders, 1 sword spider&lt;br&gt;\nGiant Spider (4 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 15, DEX 17, CON 12, INT -, WIS 10, CHA 2; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 32, AC 6, THAC0 16, Saving Throws 10/13/10/13/13&lt;br&gt;\n1 Attack Per Round, 1d8 Piercing Damage (Bite +1)&lt;br&gt;\nSword Spider (5 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 17, DEX 10, CON 15, INT -, WIS 11, CHA 3; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 45, AC 3, THAC0 14, Saving Throws 9/12/9/12/12&lt;br&gt;\n4 Attacks Per Round, 1d8+2 Piercing Damage (Legs &amp; Bite +1)&lt;br&gt;\nCombat Abilities (all spiders):&lt;br&gt;\nPoison: spiders\u2019 bites inject a venom which inflicts 3hp/round for 1 turn (save vs. poison negates)&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Qualities (all spiders):&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to poison &amp; web effects"}
{"id": "4359", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4359", "title": "Spider Wood", "text": "Spiders and spider-relatives are common enemies in Spider Wood, which is part of the &lt;a href=\"Wood%20of%20Sharp%20Teeth\"&gt;Wood of Sharp Teeth&lt;/a&gt;. But strangely enough, not all of them respawn; the &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Spider\"&gt;Sword Spider&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20Spider\"&gt;Wraith Spider&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"Ettercap\"&gt;Ettercap&lt;/a&gt;s within the three traps area only live once, and are not replaced on future visits. But &lt;a href=\"Huge%20Spider\"&gt;Huge Spider&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Tasloi\"&gt;Tasloi&lt;/a&gt;, and Ettercaps and Giant Spiders elsewhere respawn.\nConnections.\nThe entire eastern zone wall is a rocky escarpment and cannot be used to connect to or travel to other areas. The north edge is similarly impassable except in the north-western corner, although entry from the north brings you to a spot midway along the northern border.\nIn the one lands in the north western part and can exit north once &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt; is available.\nWeb traps.\nThese traps are exceedingly wide. Since characters can not walk in a completely straight line, if the &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt; is at one end of the trap and is directed to disarm the trap, they may set them off by walking to the central 'disarming point', even when Detect Traps is on and the traps have been detected and are displayed in red outline. Better to manually direct the character's movement to the center.\nEncounters.\nThe Ettercap has the scroll even before the party speaks with Fahrington; it looks like a Protection from Cold scroll.\nIf Edwin is in the party, Denak will then speak the following lines and the four will disappear; if not, the four will attack.\nRest may be disturbed by Giant Spiders.\nGameplay.\nOriginal BG1.\nThose seeking to farm the Phase Spiders and the like are out of luck; as the same is true of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%23Second%20Cloakwood\"&gt;second Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; forest, there is no way to farm them in BG1. This makes Wyverns in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%23Fourth%20Cloakwood\"&gt;fourth Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; forest not only the ultimate (because of the &lt;a href=\"Wyvern%20Head\"&gt;Wyvern Head&lt;/a&gt;s that can be sold to &lt;a href=\"Officer%20Vai\"&gt;Officer Vai&lt;/a&gt;), but the only high-XP farming opportunity, with few easier ways with which to prepare for them.\nEnhanced Edition.\nIn the enhanced edition farming experience is not much of an issue as one has access to providing several high level areas to visit. Though not advised for a new party, these areas can be visited as early as chapter one."}
