{"id": "5870", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5870", "title": "Spook", "text": "The Spook spell allows the wizard to play upon the natural fears of the target creature. \nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a single creature using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the spell cast is finished, a sparkling projectile travels unerringly to the target and exposes it to the spell's effects.\nThe target is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell to resist the effects of the \"Spook\" - the saving throw has incremental penalties based upon the caster's mage level, ranging between -1 to -6 modifiers.\nif the save is failed, then the victim will show a brief lighting effect and color fade rendered on their sprite, and a text will display reading \"Spook\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the victim is spooked, and another will sound when the spell duration expires.\nIf a player character is affected by this spell, an icon (No. 36) titled \"Panic\" will show on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nThis spell induces the &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; status effect on a creature that fails its &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt;, lasting 3-rounds.\nThe spell is negated by a creature protected with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Illusion&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; also has a chance to block it.\nA creature with any &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense can also block the \"Spook\" spell.\nThe spell can be removed by any applicable &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nBe aware that a caster that has an active &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight/Seeing&lt;/a&gt; spell in effect will remove the spook spell from a hostile creature, as well casting a &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Illusion\"&gt;Detect Illusion&lt;/a&gt; spell - a text will display reading \"Illusion Dispelled\".\nNote that Illusionists may cast this spell with potentially up to -8 (-6 and then the kit's -2) save penalty once they reach level 12.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Spook\" is very similar to the BG Video game version, except for its duration. However, in the PnP game the victim is allowed a saving throw each round they are affected (with no penalties) to recognize that an illusion is occurring, and the spell is over only when that occurs. The spell only works on creatures with at least 2 intelligence and won't affect the undead.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration and saving throw scaling. See below for description:\nSpook\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Illusion\nRange: Long\nDuration: 5 rounds\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Special\nA Spook spell enables the wizard to play upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the spellcaster as someone or something inimical which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful saving throw vs. spell, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wizard as possible. The creature has a saving throw penalty of -1 (to save against this spell) for every two extra experience levels of the caster, to a maximum of -4 at 9th level. Although the caster does not actually pursue the fleeing creature, a phantasm from its own mind does. Undead creatures, certain powerful creatures who can easily discern the illusion, such as dragons, and those with no intelligence score are unaffected by this spell, as are creatures under the effect of a True Seeing spell."}
{"id": "50293", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50293", "title": "Spore Colony", "text": "A Spore Colony is a &lt;a href=\"fungus\"&gt;fungoid&lt;/a&gt;, intelligent creature that is &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt; aligned although it may react with hostility if a stranger approaches. Like &lt;a href=\"Myconid\"&gt;Myconid&lt;/a&gt;s, it has an aversion to sunlight and is most often found in caves or other subterranean locations. It uses no weapons nor carries any treasure.\nTheir appearance is that of a bloated fungus with four tentacle-like appendages that sprout from the central core of the creature. Four more tentacle-like appendages are located around the base of the creature; however, they don't appear to provide anything more than a means of stability as, unlike Myconids, a Spore Colony is completely stationary. They look exactly like a &lt;a href=\"Shrieker\"&gt;Shrieker&lt;/a&gt; and the only method of differentiating between the two is through their actions when approached by a hostile creature.\nCombat.\nThe Spore Colony does not have the Myconid &lt;a href=\"confusion\"&gt;confusion&lt;/a&gt;-inducing attack. Instead, it will blast out a cloud of spores which will \"summon\" two Myconid creatures. The summoned spore creature is an actual Myconid, and as such cannot be banished with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. The spore cloud is triggered 10 seconds after a hostile creature is within detection range.\nThe \"ICFUNG02.cre\" will continue to blast out two more Myconids every 20 seconds until an overall total of four summon events have transpired or the Spore Colony has been killed, while the \"ICFUNGUS.cre\" will blast out the same number of Myconids at the same rate until an overall total of six summon events have transpired or the Spore Colony has been killed.\n\"Note: In the &lt;a href=\"Myconid%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Myconid Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area, once the Spore Colony is killed, any remaining Myconids will also drop dead.\"\nSpore Colonies will not engage in any type of melee attack as they are unable to utilize the undroppable attack &lt;a href=\"UMBER01.ITM\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; they possess. However, the weapon still provides immunity to any confusion effects cast upon them."}
{"id": "51316", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51316", "title": "Spore Room (Spellhold Test)", "text": "This area is technically part of &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe fungi laden cavern will be a location that the party is transferred to by the &lt;a href=\"Apparition%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Apparition&lt;/a&gt;, depending on how they replied to statements and questions in the &lt;a href=\"Kobold%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Kobold Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;. Basically, if the party was compliant and reasonable or non-threatening in their response to the Apparition, then they'll be transported here.\nAs soon as the party arrives in a cloud animation, the lone &lt;a href=\"Spore%20Colony\"&gt;Spore Colony&lt;/a&gt; creature will attack, there is a short delay before it can activate its special innate power (see the creature page for details). The party should be able to fell the sentient fungus before it can initiate the ability.\nOnce the hostile being is dispatched, another appearance of the Apparition takes place. He initiates dialogue and poses another test, involving a riddle that must be answered by selecting from a listing of multiple-choice answers. If the correct answer is given, the Apparition makes a convoluted remark, saying:\nIf the party gives the incorrect answer to the riddle, the Apparition says:\nOn the other hand, if the party says \"\"What is this? I do not understand your question.\" the Apparition replies: \nThe party can then select from a menu of answers:&lt;br&gt;\n\"I refuse to answer your questions. You have no business knowing my mind\". - The Apparition replies: \"I offer civilized discourse, and you counter with obstinance. Unfortunate. Your path is the hard one.\"\" - Transported to &lt;a href=\"Cave%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Cave (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt; \n\"\"I see the fertile earth that deserves respect. From this all else springs.\" - The Apparition replies: \"Perhaps a bit too much praise, but the thought is peaceful and appealing. You show the proper reverence. The path shall be easier.\"\" - Transported to &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Trap%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Crushing Trap Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n\"\"I get my food from the market. I have nothing to take from this place.\" - The Apparition replies: \"And if the market were to close? You show an unwillingness to change. Not good. The path will be a little harder.\"\" - Transported to &lt;a href=\"Cave%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Cave (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Anyone could take what they wished from here. Better it were fenced in.\" - The Apparition replies: \"Constrained, controlled, and combative. Perhaps a bit paranoid. Not good. You are not acting receptively. The path grows harder. I wouldn't want to encourage this behavior.\"\" - Transported to &lt;a href=\"Cave%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Cave (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\n\"\"I am not familiar with farming. I would need help judging it.\" - The Apparition replies: \"Open to new ideas while acknowledging failings. A good sign. Perhaps you are not lost after all. We shall see. The path is a little easier.\"\" - Transported to &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Trap%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Crushing Trap Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nIf &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen\"&gt;Jan Jansen&lt;/a&gt; is in the party, the party won't even have an opportunity to select any desired answers. When the main question is asked \"When you look to the ground, what do you see?\" Jan shouts \"Turnips!\", the Apparition says \"What? \" - Jan explains, \"Turnips! I see the soil that could keep a man in tubers for life. Of course, I guess its more for &lt;CHARNAME&gt; to say.\" The apparition will respond:\nIf the party responds with a threat of violence and refuses to answer the riddle, then the path will be more difficult.\nContainers.\nThere are two non-visible spaces that are containers in this area. One contains a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;. Grab the loot before being transported from the encounter by the Apparition."}
