{"id": "4056", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4056", "title": "Staff Mace", "text": "The Staff Mace +2 is a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt; which can transform into a mace, although when wielded it is a mace always, even for mages. This weapon has the properties of both staff (range 2ft) and mace (one-handed); it is a weapon which can be wielded in one hand and be used by anyone, except Monks.\nGameplay.\nOne of this weapon's advantages over something like a regular mace is the 2ft. range for a 1-handed weapon. This can be particularly useful for dual-wielding characters, as only the range of the mainhand weapon is considered in that case. So, for example, if a character wields this weapons along with a dagger in the offhand (range 1ft), they'll still be able to attack from range 2 (similar to a quarterstaff, that can, say, reach from behind another party member).\nThe above information is especially powerful for hit-and-run tactics and even more so when combined with a character who can lower the weapon's already-decent initial speed factor (2) down to 0 and/or gain additional attacks-per-round. Speed factor, extra attacks-per-round and range are all important considerations for characters trying to attack before their enemies and this weapon excels in two of those (but doesn't give any extra APR)."}
