{"id": "8201", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8201", "title": "Staff of Air", "text": "The Staff of Air is introduced in and .\nGameplay.\nThis weapon is basically a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt; with some unique elemental plane of air powers imbued into it.\nAs a general melee weapon, it can inflict 1d6+2 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, with a 2-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, and a reach of 2-feet as well as a speed factor of 2.\nIf the staff strikes a creature with a Class identifier of , each hit has a chance to apply a &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect, which can be negated with a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell.\nSummon Air Elemental ability.\nOnce per 8-hour rest, the wielder may summon an 8-hit die Lesser Air Elemental for 1-hour. \nTo summon an elemental, select the \"Use Item\" button on the character record, choose the appropriate icon, then place a targeting cursor on the area map where the elemental will spawn. There is a 20' range to this function.\nThe creature summoned is SUMELAIR.CRE detailed at the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Lesser Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; page, but a summary is included below:\nLesser Air Elemental (8 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 19, DEX 9, CON 9, INT9, WIS 9, CHA 9; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 64, AC 2, THAC0 10, Saving Throws 10/12/11/12/13&lt;br&gt;\n1 Attack Per Round, 1d20+7 Crushing Damage (Fist +3)\nSpecial Qualities:&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to weapons less than +2 enchantment&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Air%20Elemental%20Whirlwind\"&gt;Air Elemental Whirlwind&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nSleep Cloud ability.\nThe staff also is found with the ability to expend a charge and produce a \"Sleep Cloud\" - the staff can hold up to 10 charges, and can be recharged by selling to a vendor, and buying it back - If however, all the charges from the staff are used up, this feature is disabled until it is recharged.\nThe sleep cloud is employed by selecting the \"Use Item\" button/tab on the character record and selecting the appropriate icon, then placing the targeting cursor to designate the target point for the cloud projectile to travel towards on the area map - there is a 40' range to this projectile.\nThe sleep cloud projectile flies to the target point and then quickly expands into a 15' feet radius cloud, remaining for 1-turn.\nAll creatures (friend or foe) within the cloud must make a saving throw versus death each round they are inside the cloud.\nA failed saving throw results in the victim being made &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; for three rounds - the combat log will display a text reading \"Unconscious\" for each creature that is affected.\nWhile the victim is unconscious, it is also &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;, and damaging the creature won't result in them being revived/awakened. \nThe sleep cloud can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but it is a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 0 effect, and thus isn't subject to a protection like &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; - however, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; will block the cloud's effects.\nCreatures with the race &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-elf&lt;/a&gt; get a chance to resist this cloud at a probability of 90% and 30% respectively.\nA &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt; will disperse this cloud.\nNote.\nMultiple applications of this cloud can be \"stacked\" in the same area, causing multiple exposures and requiring multiple saving throws to resist it.\nThe Sleep Cloud is not flagged as a \"Hostile\" spell.\nThe Sleep Cloud is assigned to the Enchantment spell school, and has a secondary type classification of \"Disabling\".\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, The respective Staves of Air/Earth/Fire could charm their respective elementals, however, the sound that accompanied the charm would play on all targets even if they weren't subject to the charm itself. This is identified for correction in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP). Ref: (staf15.itm, staf16.itm, staf17.itm)"}
