{"id": "8228", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8228", "title": "Staff of Command", "text": "The Staff of Command is a special &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt; introduced in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 5&lt;/a&gt; only.\nAquisition.\nIt can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; area, stored in a piece of illthid furniture.\nGameplay.\nThe weapon inflicts 1d6 +2 points of crushing damage, has -2 THAC0 bonus and a speed factor of 3. It weighs 3 lbs. and it requires at least 5 strength to wield. Only &lt;a href=\"monk\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt;s cannot wield this weapon.\nThe staff's most amazing power is the ability to expend a charge - and then launch a projectile at a single target in a 40' range. Once the projectile reaches the target the creature is exposed to a potent &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt; effect. There is no saving throw allowed. \nIf the Dire Charm effect is successful, then the creature is affected for 12 hours (!). Once the duration is expired or if the creature is attacked by the party, or the effect dispelled - the creature will be freed of the charm and hostile to the caster/party. \nThe staff's Dire Charm is a 5 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; effect, and thus can be stopped by several Spell Protections, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this effect, as will &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreatures immune to &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; effects will be protected from this staff's ability. Elves and Half elves are resistant to it as well.\nThe staff has a 25-charge capacity. If all the charges are used up, the staff will be disabled."}
{"id": "8089", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8089", "title": "Staff of Curing", "text": "The Staff of Curing is a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B1\"&gt;Quarterstaff +1&lt;/a&gt; with an ability that can be used 10 times to restore 3d6 + 3 hit points and remove the &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;intoxication&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt;. The staff can be recharged like a wand, as long as the charges are not taken all the way down to zero.\nLocation.\nIt can be found in a &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20%28near%20Arenthis%20%26amp%3B%20Risa%29\"&gt;crypt&lt;/a&gt; in the southeast corner of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; district."}
{"id": "9588", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9588", "title": "Staff of Earth", "text": "The Staff of Earth is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt;. It can inflict 1d6 +2 points of crushing damage and has &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of -2. It weighs 3 lbs and has a speed factor of 2. A successful hit with the weapon can also slay any that fails to save vs. Spell with the instant death effect bypassing Magic Resistance. And it has two rechargeable abilities: It can be used to summon a &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Lesser Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; and to revert a &lt;a href=\"Petrified\"&gt;Petrified status effect&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nBy expending a charge, the wielder may summon an 8-hit die Lesser Earth Elemental \"(SUMELEAR.cre)\" for one hour. The summoned creature will attack any enemy within a range of 20 feet. The staff has a maximum of 30 charges for this function. \nThe wielder may also use a charge to produce a Stone to Flesh effect\u00a0that reverts the petrification of a creature. This has a touch range. The revert process is implemented by the staff using an Opcode 43 Cure Stone to Flesh, along with some graphic animation and sound effects. The staff has a maximum of 30 charges for this function. \nOnce the charges in the staff are consumed, the staff will not be destroyed, but the charged abilities are disabled. The staff can be sold to a merchant, where it will recharge like a wand, and then purchased (or stolen if applicable) to use its abilities again. \nIt can be bought exclusively from the Drow &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20Merchant%20%28Ust%20Natha%20Bazaar%29\"&gt;weapons merchant&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha%20Bazaar\"&gt;Ust Natha Bazaar&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, The respective Staves of Air/Earth/Fire could charm their respective elementals, however, the sound that accompanied the charm would play on all targets even if they weren't subject to the charm itself. This is identified for correction in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP). Ref: (staf15.itm, staf16.itm, staf17.itm)"}
