{"id": "14707", "revid": "285258", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14707", "title": "Staff of Power", "text": "The Staff of Power is a unique Quarterstaff +2 which can only be used by classes that can cast mage spells.\nGameplay.\nIt can be created by your apprentices during the Mage Stronghold Quest &lt;a href=\"Claiming%20the%20Sphere\"&gt;Claiming the Sphere&lt;/a&gt; in and .\nYour apprentices will need 10.000 gold. However it is not certain that they will be able to create the item, and all of them will surely die in the attempt.\nIt grants the user +2 to &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; and saving throws. &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and Lightning Bolt of Paralyzation (10d6 electrical damage to all in path; stuns target for 5 rounds, no save, blocked by magic resistance; range: 100\u00a0ft.) can be used as charge abilities. They both consume one charge.\nThe Lightning Bolt of Paralyzation is blocked by minor globe of invulnerability and spell deflection (taking 3 charges off per bounce of bolt).\nGiven its description, it can be assumed that it may have been an existing item to be found or obtained, and not built from scratch through crafting by your apprentices."}
{"id": "6737", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6737", "title": "Staff of Rhynn", "text": "Staff of Rhynn +4 is a Quarterstaff with +4 enchantment, with corresponding +4 bonus to damage and -4 bonus &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, as well as speed factor of 1.\nIt is sold exclusively by &lt;a href=\"Ribald%20Barterman\"&gt;Ribald Barterman&lt;/a&gt; in his normal stock.\nGameplay.\nThis staff is by far the most easily obtainable +4 weapon in the game, allowing one to try one's luck against &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx&lt;/a&gt; as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;."}
