{"id": "4060", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4060", "title": "Staff of Striking", "text": "The Staff of Striking (Staff of Striking +3 in-game) is a quarterstaff with 25 charges when fully charged, and will destroy itself when there are no charges left. As with all items with a fixed number of charges, it is possible to recharge this weapon. Simply sell it to a store and then buy it back.\nIf you look at the statistics of the weapon, it has almost the same as a &lt;a href=\"Aule%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Quarterstaff +3&lt;/a&gt;, but has a damage bonus of +9, which is six points higher.\nIn \"\", it is the most powerful staff and probably the strongest blunt weapon available. It's also in a different proficiency compared to other games. \nIn \" &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Ram\"&gt;Staff of the Ram&lt;/a&gt; is a more powerful staff, but the Staff of Striking is considerably easier to obtain very early in the game. &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstabbing&lt;/a&gt; characters (i.e. most &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"stalker\"&gt;stalkers&lt;/a&gt;) should purchase it as soon as possible, as it will likely be their strongest backstabbing weapon for much of the game."}
