{"id": "12332", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12332", "title": "Staff of the Ram", "text": "The Staff of the Ram is a quarterstaff that has a chance of knocking back and stunning the enemy. This does not work against dragons, giants or other large creatures.\nIt is similar to a &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Striking\"&gt;Staff of Striking&lt;/a&gt; but it is more powerful and does not use charges. Its creator might be the same of the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Ram\"&gt;Ring of the Ram&lt;/a&gt;.\nStaff of the Ram +4.\nGameplay Staff +4.\nThe weapon is a +4 enchanted quarterstaff with a reach of 2 feet, and a weapon speed factor of 1.\nEach successful hit can inflict 1d6+10 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the weapon provides a 4 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nThere is a 10% chance of the blow causing the targeted creature to be exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt;/knockback effect, which lasts 2 seconds and pushes the creature away from the wielder up to 20 feet distance.\nAt the same time, the knockback \"stuns\" the target, lasting 6 seconds. This is actually an &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; status effect rather than a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThe knockback and stun can't be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, spell protections, and has no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt;, nor can it be dispelled.\nThe knockback effect is sub-coded to not work against very large creatures such as a dragon or giant/ettin etc.\nStaff of the Ram +6.\nGameplay Staff +6.\nThe upgraded weapon is a +6 enchanted quarterstaff with a reach of 2 deet, and a weapon speed factor of 1.\nEach successful hit can inflict 1d6+12 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, plus 1d4 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the weapon provides a 6 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nThere is a 15% chance of the blow causing the targeted creature to be exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt;/knockback effect, which lasts 2 seconds and pushes the creature away from the wielder up to 20 feet distance.\nAt the same time, the knockback \"stuns\" the target, lasting 6 seconds. This is actually an &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; status effect rather than a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nThe knockback and stun can't be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, spell protections, and has no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt;, nor can it be dispelled.\nThere is a reported problem as of EE 2.6 with how the +6 staff responds to large creatures struck. It apparently needs a fix to make it not apply the knockback effect to large creatures.\nNotes.\nThis staff is probably the highest damaging weapon for &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Backstabbing\"&gt;backstabbing&lt;/a&gt;, similar to a &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Striking\"&gt;Staff of Striking&lt;/a&gt; but more powerful and without use of charges.\nThere is a higher damaging &lt;a href=\"Shapechange\"&gt;Shapechange&lt;/a&gt; form that can outperform peak backstab damage from this staff, but from a wielded actual weapon viewpoint, the Staff of the Ram +6 is king of backstab damage potential.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, The knockback effect of the Staff of the Ram +6 should not work on large creatures. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. Ref: (staf22.itm)"}
