{"id": "8264", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8264", "title": "Starfall Ore", "text": "Starfall Ore is an component needed to upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Star\"&gt;Storm Star&lt;/a&gt;. The mace has to brought to &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; who can then upgrade the item.\nThis item appears in and .\nLocation.\nThe ore can be found in &lt;a href=\"Kiser%20Jhaeri\"&gt;Kiser Jhaeri&lt;/a&gt;'s house in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "26278", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26278", "title": "Starting equipment", "text": "When the &lt;a href=\"Character%20Generation\"&gt;Character Generation&lt;/a&gt; is done and the game commences, the &lt;a href=\"protagonist\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt; will or will not find themselves equipped with some initial \u2013 this depends on \"which\" is played. This article gives detailed information on what to find in your character's backpack, ordered chronologically.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;\n\"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEvery newly generated character is equipped with a &lt;a href=\"quarterstaff\"&gt;quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt; and nothing else.\nThere is no extra character generation for the first game's original add-on. However, in the classic edition a predefined savegame, the \"Mission-Pack-Save\" may be chosen as a starting point, with a predefined &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; who comes already equipped. This savegame was removed from the \".\nEquipment for new, non-&lt;a href=\"Importing\"&gt;imported&lt;/a&gt; characters is assigned by the script for the &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%20Family%20Tomb%20First%20Floor\"&gt;starting area&lt;/a&gt;, codice_1. Exact equipment varies based on &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;ability scores&lt;/a&gt;, chosen &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiencies&lt;/a&gt;, and possibly more.\nNewly generated characters in the second part of the series have no equipment at all when starting the game, but may find some during the course of the first chapters, that most likely would have belonged to a &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; which made her way from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nNewly generated characters who have \"not\" been &lt;a href=\"Importing\"&gt;imported&lt;/a&gt; from the \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign will start the add-on with some powerful equipment, based on their &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; and the game file codice_2.\n&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nShields.\nNo new character will be equipped with a .\nAmmunition.\nAll classes, except &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Brown%20Bear\"&gt;Grizzly Bear&lt;/a&gt;, have stocks of the following :\nPotions.\nAll classes, except the &lt;a href=\"Brown%20Bear\"&gt;Grizzly Bear&lt;/a&gt;, will find the following in their &lt;a href=\"inventory\"&gt;inventory&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "29000", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29000", "title": "Statue", "text": ""}
{"id": "55581", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55581", "title": "Statue (GORSTA01)", "text": "Statue GORSTA01 has an appearance of a Human male fighter wearing helmet, plate mail and wielding a bastard sword and medium shield. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the first initial (2-4) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis fighter will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature behaves as an ordinary human fighter and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nOnly the bastard sword is recoverable from his slain body.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default tactical fighter script is provided. His experience level is raised to 21. The fighter has a use of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; scripted for use.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nThree ready to use potions are provided for the warrior to boost abilities or heal wounds when hit points fall to a preset threshold."}
{"id": "55582", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55582", "title": "Statue (GORSTA02)", "text": "Statue GORSTA02 has an appearance of an Elven male fighter wearing helmet, plate mail and wielding a halberd. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the first initial (2-4) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis fighter will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature behaves as an ordinary fighter and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nNo items are recoverable from his slain body.\nNote.\nThe creature file has assigned 5 pips in Bastard Sword and 2 pips in sword and shield style to this elf. Probably a near copy-paste of GORSTA01. There are legacy stat proficiencies for spear in the file, so this elf is only \"specialized\" in halberd use. This is probably just a coding omission.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default tactical fighter script is provided. His experience level is raised to 21. The fighter has a use of &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Greater Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; scripted for use.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nSCS adjusts a probable coding omission that the base game has and reconfigures the elf to have 5 pips to Halberd weapon proficiency and 2 pips for two-handed weapon fighting style.\nThree ready to use potions are provided for the warrior to boost abilities or heal wounds when hit points fall to a preset threshold."}
{"id": "55583", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55583", "title": "Statue (GORSTA03)", "text": "Statue GORSTA03 has an appearance of an Elven female cleric wearing plate mail and wielding a mace. She's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the first initial (2-4) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis cleric will begin combat by self-buffing with &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt; instantly applied.\nFurther spell casting is scripted, most of which are interruptible, as shown in the InfoBox.\nShe has the ability to cast &lt;a href=\"Creeping%20Doom\"&gt;Creeping Doom&lt;/a&gt;, as several of the Knights of the Vigil do, such as &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Garlena\"&gt;Sister Garlena&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf she is pressed upon by a party member in melee range, she can engage in melee combat with her mace, although she is a cleric and has only 1 attack per round.\nThe creature mostly behaves as a spell casting cleric and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nNo items are recoverable from her slain body.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default smarter priest script is provided. \nRace is changed to Golem.\nShe gets a different spell book of divine magic scripted for use.\nHer opening chain of defensive buffs is &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther spell casting and summoning of allies is based on how her AI script assesses the party's protections and threats.\nA ready to use potion is provided for the cleric to boost abilities."}
{"id": "55584", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55584", "title": "Statue (GORSTA04)", "text": "Statue GORSTA04 has an appearance of a Dwarven male cleric wearing plate mail and wielding a mace. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the first initial (2-4) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis cleric will begin combat by self-buffing with &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt; instantly applied.\nFurther spell casting is scripted, most of which are interruptible, as shown in the InfoBox.\nHe has the ability to cast &lt;a href=\"Creeping%20Doom\"&gt;Creeping Doom&lt;/a&gt;, as several of the Knights of the Vigil do, such as &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Garlena\"&gt;Sister Garlena&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf he is pressed upon by a party member in melee range, he can engage in melee combat with his mace, although he is a cleric and has only 1 attack per round.\nThe creature mostly behaves as a spell casting cleric and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nNo items are recoverable from his slain body.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default smarter priest script is provided. \nRace is changed to Golem. \nHe gets a different spell book of divine magic scripted for use.\nHis opening chain of defensive buffs is &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther spell casting and summoning of allies is based on how his AI script assesses the party's protections and threats.\nA ready to use potion is provided for the cleric to boost abilities."}
{"id": "55585", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55585", "title": "Statue (GORSTA05)", "text": "Statue GORSTA05 has an appearance of a Human female fighter wearing helmet, plate mail and wielding a bastard sword and medium shield. She's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis fighter will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature behaves as an ordinary human fighter and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nSome arms and armor are recoverable from her slain body.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default tactical fighter script is provided. Her experience level is raised to 21. The fighter has a use of &lt;a href=\"Power%20Attack\"&gt;Power Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; scripted for use.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nThree ready to use potions are provided for the warrior to boost abilities or heal wounds when hit points fall to a preset threshold."}
{"id": "55586", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55586", "title": "Statue (GORSTA06)", "text": "Statue GORSTA06 has an appearance of a Hobgoblin. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis creature will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature looks like a humanoid creature with no visible held weaponry or armor worn. The Hobgoblin appearance belies the actual attacks which are similar to that of an adult &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;, including a poisonous tail sting.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod completely changes this creature to a Human male level 25 mage (16,000 XP). Upon installation of the mod a mage kit will be randomly assigned (Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer). The mage kit assigned determines the new revised AI mage script and scripted spells used by the creature.\nExpect a chain on instantly deployed buffs, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlso, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/arcane/level-5/mestils-acid-sheath\"&gt;\"Mesthil's Acid Sheath \"&lt;/a&gt; with the SR mod.\nThe mage will also have prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; ready for scripted conditional use.\nAs this is a Throne of Bhaal dungeon, the mage will use various mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe mage is equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B1\"&gt;Quarterstaff +1&lt;/a&gt; and has a potion to quaff for healing damage.\nThe creature is also provided with several immunities: &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale break&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlenty of spells will be scripted to remove party protections, they'll be a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, and potential use of several level 8 and 9 spells.\nThis creature may be the most dangerous one of all the statues present."}
{"id": "55587", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55587", "title": "Statue (GORSTA07)", "text": "Statue GORSTA07 has an appearance of a Human male thief wearing leather armor and wielding a Ninjat\u014d. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis creature has the typical thief animation, but is actually a fighter class warrior.\nThis fighter will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature behaves as an ordinary human fighter and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nOnly &lt;a href=\"Usuno%27s%20Blade\"&gt;Usuno's Blade&lt;/a&gt; is recoverable from his slain body.\nNote.\nThe creature file has assigned 5 pips in Bastard Sword and 2 pips in sword and shield style. Probably a near copy-paste of GORSTA01. There are legacy stat proficiencies for large sword in the file, so this fighter is only \"specialized\" in Scimitar/Wakizashi/Ninjat\u014d use. This is probably just a coding omission.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default tactical fighter script is provided. His experience level is raised to 25. the creature is changed to Thief class, with a &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt; kit. This creature is some kind of fervent ninja warrior.\nThe hybrid warrior is scripted to employ &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability and the &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Assassination\"&gt;Assassination&lt;/a&gt;.\nThree pips in Scimitar/Wakazashi/Ninjat\u014d weapon proficiency is provided.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nThree ready to use potions are provided for the hybrid to boost abilities or heal wounds when hit points fall to a preset threshold."}
{"id": "55588", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55588", "title": "Statue (GORSTA08)", "text": "Statue GORSTA08 has an appearance of Iron Golem. It's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis creature has the typical Iron Golem animation, most status effect immunities that the golem type usually possesses, but in some ways is less protected from elemental and magic.\nThe golem will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe golem is not scripted to use the Iron Golem gas cloud attack ability.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. The creature is provided some immunities golems should have, including to &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, the creature is protected against &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; spells."}
{"id": "55589", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55589", "title": "Statue (GORSTA09)", "text": "Statue GORSTA09 has an appearance of an Elven male fighter wearing plate mail and wielding a Longbow. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis fighter will engage in bow and arrow fire toward the closest party member detected, attempting to keep his distance. If engaged in close quarters combat, he'll switch to Halberd.\nThe creature behaves as an ordinary fighter and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nAll of the arms and armor are recoverable from his slain body.\nNote.\nThe creature file has assigned 5 pips in Bastard Sword and 2 pips in sword and shield style to this elf. Probably a near copy-paste of GORSTA01. There are legacy stat proficiencies for spear and bow weapons in the file, so this elf is only \"specialized\" in halberd and bow use. This is probably just a coding omission.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default tactical fighter script is provided. His experience level is raised to 21. The fighter has a use of &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Greater Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; scripted for use.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nSCS adjusts a probable coding omission that the base game has and reconfigures the elf to have 5 pips to Halberd and Longbow weapon proficiency and 1 pip for two-handed weapon fighting style.\nThree ready to use potions are provided for the warrior to boost abilities or heal wounds when hit points fall to a preset threshold."}
{"id": "55590", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55590", "title": "Statue (GORSTA10)", "text": "Statue GORSTA10 has an appearance of a Gnoll. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis creature will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature looks like a humanoid creature with no visible held weaponry or armor worn. The Gnoll appearance belies the actual attacks which are similar to that of an &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulk&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes no changes to this creature, which is only mentioned here for the sake of documenting that the editor didn't miss this creature's SCS mod content."}
{"id": "55591", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55591", "title": "Statue (GORSTA11)", "text": "Statue GORSTA11 has an appearance of an Elven female mage wearing a enchanted robe and wielding a dagger. She's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis mage will initially be able to launch self-buff for protection and then continue to cast spells to remove illusions, summon allies, attack party members and further protect herself as the battle continues. See the InfoBox for most of her scripted spell casting. Expect a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Symbol, Stun (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; attack.\nThe creature behaves as a high-level mage and can fail morale checks and will call for help if needed.\nOnly the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B3\"&gt;Dagger +3&lt;/a&gt; is recoverable from her slain body.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature. A new default Smarter mage AI script is provided. She has a revised spell book, which is based on the random mage specialty kit assigned when the mod is installed - could be Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer.\nUpon hostilities commencing, she will apply a chain of spells, such as: &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;. With the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod she'll also have &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, \"Mesthil's Acid Sheath\", and \"Mind Blank\".\nThe mage has prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; for instant release.\nMage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; can be used, probably &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;.\nRace is changed to Golem.\nA potion is placed in her inventory for use to heal damage at a predetermined threshold."}
{"id": "55592", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55592", "title": "Statue (GORSTA12)", "text": "Statue GORSTA12 has an appearance of an Ogre. He's found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt; near to the Altar.\nGameplay.\nPart of the second activated group (4 - 8) &lt;a href=\"Statues%20%28WK%20Altar%20Level%29\"&gt;Statues (WK Altar Level)&lt;/a&gt; that attack the party based on actions taken at the Altar and interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20%28Altar%29\"&gt;Altar Guardian spirit&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis creature will move toward the closest party member detected and engage in melee combat until destroyed or incapacitated.\nThe creature looks like a humanoid creature with no visible held weaponry or armor worn. The Ogre appearance belies the actual attacks which are similar to that of a &lt;a href=\"Salamander\"&gt;Salamander&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to the creature so it can benefit from spear weapon proficiency, assigning 5 pips. Two pips are also given for two-handed weapon fighting style."}
{"id": "4488", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4488", "title": "Statue item riddle", "text": "Within a chamber located within &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%201\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 1&lt;/a&gt; and part of the &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt; questline in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt; is a group of eleven statues adjacent to the room's walls, as well as a single chest set on the floor that can be opened.\nDescription.\nWithin the chest are eleven items, as well as a scroll titled the \"Warden's Note\". Reading the Note, has the following text:\nThe eleven items (not including the Note) which are found in the chest are:\nGameplay.\nAlthough the note does not explicitly provide instructions of what to do, as it is a test of the inmate's mental faculties, the observant player may notice that each statue is posed in a position holding an empty bowl, as if ready to receive an item.\nAdditionally, if the player hovers the game cursor over an individual statue and interacts by clicking the \"question mark\" - then a text message will display a riddle. Each riddle is a clue as to what item best matches with the statue's riddle. \nAn item from the chest should be removed and taken into a party members inventory, and that member should transfer the item desired to the statue's bowl. \nIf all eleven items are correctly placed in each corresponding statue, a reward of 20,000 party shared XP is awarded, and within the chest is placed a &lt;a href=\"Dusty%20Rose%20Ioun%20Stone\"&gt;Dusty Rose Ioun Stone&lt;/a&gt; and a special Sapphire Stone.\nIf you are having difficulty, and need assistance, see the &lt;a href=\"Solving%20the%20statues%20riddle\"&gt;Solving the statues riddle&lt;/a&gt; article. Visiting that page can make the Warden concerned about the bhaalspawn's problem solving capabilities."}
{"id": "38059", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38059", "title": "Statue of Sel\u00fbne", "text": "The Statue of Sel\u00fbne seems to be cut content from , as nothing else links to it."}
{"id": "29001", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29001", "title": "Statues", "text": ""}
{"id": "55574", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55574", "title": "Statues (WK Altar Level)", "text": "This page is to add a gateway link page to document the various \"Statues\" located on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe statues are some kind of defensive ward put in place by the &lt;a href=\"Vigil%20Knight\"&gt;Vigil Knight&lt;/a&gt; organization. Perhaps the statues are actually volunteer creatures who will be spiritually recalled to arms if anyone attempts to open the portal to the lower reaches.\nGameplay.\nThe various statues are inert and can't be directly targeted or interacted with. This is by design. \nOnly after specific actions by the party on this dungeon level will the statues animate and turn hostile towards the party. These actions involve interacting with the Altar, and or placement and choices made regarding the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Book\"&gt;Holy Book&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bell\"&gt;Bell&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Candle\"&gt;Candle&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe statues closest to the Altar animate as one group (2 to 4 statues) determined by the party's average experience. The remaining statues animate as a second group upon triggering another event by further action at the Altar, during the Holy Ritual. \nThe statues share a common set of attributes as shown in the InfoBox. For example, they all have an innate 40% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and 50% &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance. They are all 20 Hit dice creatures, and award if defeated.\nHowever, each statue also has individual attributes, weaponry, saving throws, perhaps some droppable equipment, different classes, maybe some spell casting abilities etc. The appearances (sprite type) assigned to the statue are mostly accurate, but some are deceiving, and although a statue foe may appear as a &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin\"&gt;Hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt;, the statue's attacks can be unique, as well as it's stats.\nSetting traps, usually an effective tactic to deal damage to creatures that may spawn or activate - is mitigated and may not (probably won't) work against the statues. When the statues activate, there is a delay before they become non-statue forms. However, the traps will fire off before that, dealing no damage because the creatures still have their protective items. To use traps effectively, set them in an area further away from their statue form, and lead them into the traps. Good hunting adventurer!\nAbout the number of statues.\nThere will be at least 6 statues present in this level's main hallway leading to the Altar sector. There could be up to 12 statues present as well. The number is determined by the party's first visit to this dungeon and is tied to the party's average experience level. If the party has an average XP level equal to or greater than 14, then the full complement of statues will be here.\nIf the party has less than level 14 average experience, then there will probably be fewer statues. \nAs a reminder, &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Garlena\"&gt;Sister Garlena&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Odren\"&gt;Odren&lt;/a&gt; will warn the player to reconsider taking on their quest - if the script detects that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; doesn't have at least 10 experience levels. This gentle reminder is for the player to consider returning when the party is more appropriately tested in battle.\nSo, expect fewer statues if entering this dungeon level when the party does not meet the level design criteria for difficulty, e.g., level 14. Any statues removed by the difficulty level script check are permanently gone from the game and won't be reinserted if the party comes back to the keep later with more experience. \nThis is one downside (depending on one's viewpoint) of entering the keep at lower experience levels. As much as 120K potential XP could be missing from the adventure. Probably more actually, as the random spawns in the dungeon are also generally less difficult and have fewer XP points offered when the player enters the keep under-leveled."}
{"id": "13513", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13513", "title": "Statuette of Lathander", "text": "The Statuette of Lathander is an item in \"\". &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; will ask the party to steal the statue if the party &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; is less than 10."}
{"id": "2595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2595", "title": "Status Effects", "text": "Status Effects are positive or negative effects applied to creatures.\nImplementation.\nThe game engine implements each effect using an &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Op Code&lt;/a&gt; (Integer), and the effect from the code is actually applied to a creature as a \"State\". Examples:\nOften when a creature is affected by a State or Status Effect there will be a message in the information window that displays a \"String\" or \"String Reference\" with an associated term or words, such as \"Stunned\" or \"Paralyzed\".\nMost of the time there are also icons associated with the State or Status Effect that are displayed in the party member's portrait, such as \"Blessed\" or \"Held\". The related icons can be seen on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companions&lt;/a&gt;' portraits in user interface.\nEffects can be applied from items, &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;, creature attacks, traps, &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; or even the mere passage of &lt;a href=\"Time%20System\"&gt;time&lt;/a&gt; (e.g., &lt;a href=\"fatigue\"&gt;fatigue&lt;/a&gt;).\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nThe following status effects appear in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its expansion \"\".\nAbbreviations:\n\"Baldur's Gate II\".\nThe following status effects appear in and later games.\nEffects Interactions.\nIn the \"Enhanced Editions\", almost no &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; stack with themselves, but they do with each other. Some exceptions are:\nIn the original , many spells do stack with themselves.\n like &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Touch\"&gt;Vampiric Touch&lt;/a&gt; don't stack with their &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; equivalents."}
