{"id": "34264", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34264", "title": "Stone Dowser", "text": "The Stone Dowser is given to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Torsin%20de%20Lancie\"&gt;Torsin de Lancie&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; in . The item must be worn as a necklace to properly guide &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companions&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Barrel%20of%20Bwoosh%21\"&gt;Barrel of Bwoosh!&lt;/a&gt; drop site on the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; map in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten \u2013 Allied Siege Camp&lt;/a&gt;. The drop site is south of the &lt;a href=\"Ettin%20Ghost\"&gt;Ettin Ghost&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8940", "revid": "275052", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8940", "title": "Stone Golem", "text": "Stone Golems are constructs of intermediate power, behind &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;iron&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Adamantite%20Golem\"&gt;adamantite golems&lt;/a&gt; but potentially more powerful and durable than a &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnly +2 or greater enchanted weapons can harm them, and they are 100 % magic resistant. This golem type has no resistance to &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;. Accordingly, they can be damaged by spells or attacks that bypass magic resistance. \nThe golem's melee attack dishes out 3d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt; and it is modified by their superior strength. The fist attack counts as a +4 enchanted item for the purpose of what it can strike. They typically only strike once per round. If a Stone Golem is accompanied by a &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt;, which occurs in several areas in the saga, then they may be under the effects of &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Haste\"&gt;Golem Haste&lt;/a&gt; which doubles their movement and &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe golem's innate immunity to a number of &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; is listed in the info box. There are still a number of effects that can impede this type of golem, so be aware there are ways to cause them to be less effective with the correct items or attacks.\nLike the &lt;a href=\"Juggernaut%20Golem\"&gt;Juggernaut Golem&lt;/a&gt;, they have the innate ability to initiate a &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Slow\"&gt;Golem Slow&lt;/a&gt; effect, which is scripted to initiate when an enemy is observed, and upon the outset of hostilities.\nLocations.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nNote: \"One or two Stone Golems will be triggered by hidden proximity traps inside the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt; during Chapter 6, depending upon the current &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. It is possible that they may be accompanied by a &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Golem\"&gt;Iron&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Adamantite%20Golem\"&gt;Adamantite Golem&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"AI Enhancement's\" component improves many aspects of creatures encountered in the game. In regard to golems, the mod implements the following:\nImproved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET)&lt;br&gt;\nThis component doesn't really make golems smarter (they're supposed to be stupid) But it streamlines their scripts a bit, gives their weapons a sensible range, makes them immune to \"Lower Resistance\" and to poison, and tries to prevent situations where golems get stuck behind barricades. It also fixes an animation glitch in the Iron Golem animation - this hopefully makes iron golems a bit prettier when they attack and blow clouds.\nWith this component the stone golem is immune to the following spells and status effects: &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Slow\"&gt;Golem Slow&lt;/a&gt; innate ability is initiated at the beginning of hostilities, and again, every three rounds thereafter.\nThis golem now has a melee attack range reach of 2, instead of the unmodified creature's range of 1."}
{"id": "56104", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56104", "title": "Stone Golem (Manual)", "text": "The Stone Golem is summoned from using the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem%20Manual\"&gt;Stone Golem Manual&lt;/a&gt;. This article is about that specific creature, and not the other &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt; versions.\nThe Stone Golem Manual is only available in the original and Enhanced Edition portion of .\nGameplay.\nThe golem is a controlled creature. It is best used by the player directing its movement and who/what to target.\nWhen the golem detects an enemy creature, it will automatically attempt a &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Slow\"&gt;Golem Slow&lt;/a&gt; ability, fired over itself and potentially affecting adversaries in the area of effect.\nIf left to make decisions on its own during battle, the script it is furnished is very simplistic and may not perform to the player's liking.\nThe golem will act as a basic melee fighting creature usings its bludgeoning fists to beat on a target.\nThe golem can be useful as a distraction, especially against magic spell casting oriented creatures, such as a mage, lich, or beholder, due to its immunities and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis golem can be buffed by the party to increase its effectiveness, such as with a &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nThe golem will disappear from the map when 1 turn expires.\nA &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; will destroy/banish this golem, as its gender is \"summoned\".\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes a few revisions to this particular golem.\nThe default AI script is modified, so that if the golem is allowed by the player to do its own thing, it has a decision logic that evaluates if an enemy is protected by &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and then may try a different available target to pummel.\nIt also recognizes when its fists get a \"weapon ineffective\" result and will look for a different target.\nThe AI will cast &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Slow\"&gt;Golem Slow&lt;/a&gt; after several rounds of combat, as long as the creature is functional. Expect an initial application and then one more before the golem's duration expires.\nThe mod makes the golem immune to the spells &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt;. It is also immune to being &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;Webbed&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "56103", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56103", "title": "Stone Golem Manual", "text": "The Stone Golem Manual is manufactured from the &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem%20Manual\"&gt;Clay Golem Manual&lt;/a&gt; and restored by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane (area)&lt;/a&gt; during portion of the game.\nGameplay.\nTo restore and improve the Clay Golem Manual, the party must speak with the Imp Cespenar and have the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem%20Page\"&gt;Stone Golem Page&lt;/a&gt; in their possession, and 5,000 gold. \nOnce per rest cycle this manual may be read. The tome is placed in a character's \"Quick item\" slot (such as where a wand or scroll is placed), and then the player selects the manual and triggers the power of the item.\nNext, place a targeting cursor within 30 feet of the character to designate where the golem will appear on the map.\nA summoning animation plays at that location, and a few moments later a golem appears, in the prone position, and then it stands, ready to obey commands.\nThe golem lasts for one turn, and when time expires, disappears from the map.\nThe manual recharges and can be used again, after a standard 8-hour rest period.\nThis manual can be restored even further by the imp with the &lt;a href=\"Juggernaut%20Golem%20Page\"&gt;Juggernaut Golem Page&lt;/a&gt;. \nStone Golem Description.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem%20%28Manual%29\"&gt;Stone Golem (Manual)&lt;/a&gt; page for stats and description of the summoned creature from this manual."}
{"id": "23126", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23126", "title": "Stone Golem Page", "text": "Loot from a trapped container on the wall left of the Slave Woman in northeast corner of &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Yaga-Shura's Keep&lt;/a&gt;, Stone Golem Page is a &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;potential component&lt;/a&gt; for upgrading the &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Manual\"&gt;Golem Manual&lt;/a&gt;. The Stone Golem Page makes the Golem Manual the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem%20Manual\"&gt;Stone Golem Manual&lt;/a&gt;. This upgraded manual allows the summoning of a party controlled Stone Golem for 1 turn.\nThe actual creature summoned by the manual is TOMEGOL03.cre. Its gender is \"summoned\" (and thus can be banished by s &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. It is otherwise identical to the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt; linked on this page."}
{"id": "28135", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28135", "title": "Stone Harp", "text": "The Stone Harp is a quest item found and used during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis item can be found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Harpist%27s%20House\"&gt;The Harpist's House&lt;/a&gt; in the elven city.\nIt will be needed when the party eventually is able to enter &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithout the Stone Harp the main quest won't be able to progress - and Irenicus will be victorious in his plan to drain The Tree of Life, and worse."}
{"id": "28136", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28136", "title": "Stone Horn", "text": "The Stone Horn is a quest item found and used during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;. It isn't an optional item and must be found and used correctly to continue the main questline of the saga.\nAquisition.\nFind it in &lt;a href=\"The%20House%20of%20the%20Horn\"&gt;The House of the Horn&lt;/a&gt; within a container.\nGameplay.\nThe player will need this item in order to progress to the &lt;a href=\"Tree%20of%20Life\"&gt;Tree of Life&lt;/a&gt; from the interior of &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt;. The horn is one of two parts that serves as a \"key\" of sorts to initiate the opening of a hidden stairway within a fountain pool."}
{"id": "51288", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51288", "title": "Stone Spit", "text": "Stone Spit is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Mephit\"&gt;Earth Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A bullet projectile is launched at a single target in range. It will strike the target and inflict 1d6 damage.\nThe innate ability has no saving throw, ignores magic resistance and has level 2 spell power, and thus could be blocked by spell protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The effect can be absorbed with a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; as well."}
