{"id": "42078", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42078", "title": "Storekeep (Bridge District)", "text": "Sio'chaire is a merchant in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign. Her cart is located in the central market place, in front of the &lt;a href=\"Estate%20of%20Saerk%20Farrahd\"&gt;Estate of Saerk Farrahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn addition to selling some basic gear, she also provides a few cures at reduced prices, fencing services, and charges less for her identification skills. She is the only merchant in the game who sells &lt;a href=\"Good%20Berry\"&gt;Good Berries&lt;/a&gt;. She sells &lt;a href=\"Tangled%20Strings\"&gt;Tangled Strings&lt;/a&gt; if it was equipped or in the inventory of a character imported from Siege of Dragonspear.\nBuy and Sell.\nThe merchant is available during the day from 5:30 till 17:30 with a lunch break from 11:30 till 12:30."}
{"id": "36770", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36770", "title": "Storekeep (Potion Shop)", "text": "A &lt;a href=\"true%20neutral\"&gt;true neutral&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"innocent\"&gt;innocent&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; storekeep &lt;a href=\"Merchants\"&gt;sells&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 day in, day out \u2013 his &lt;a href=\"Potions\"&gt;wares&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;Potion Shop&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;southwest&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nThough his &lt;a href=\"store\"&gt;store&lt;/a&gt; is specialized in &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;, the storekeep himself may not be the very specialist for this subject, judging by some oddly &lt;a href=\"Murky%20potions\"&gt;murky&lt;/a&gt; bottles in the display. Perhaps this is the reason why there's no other customer visiting &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;his shop&lt;/a&gt; that he operates as an ordinary &lt;a href=\"General%20Store\"&gt;General Store&lt;/a&gt;. His pockets are as empty as his shop and the shelves inside it.\nInvolvement.\nThe storekeep sells only &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt;, but will buy some other &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s as well; see &lt;a href=\"%23STO1115\"&gt;below&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed list. He can &lt;a href=\"identify\"&gt;identify&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt;s, though for a higher-than-usual cost. For a &lt;a href=\"Rogues\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt;, it's possible to &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;steal&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"store\"&gt;store&lt;/a&gt;; if that fails, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer/FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcer&lt;/a&gt; with two &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer/FLAMEN2\"&gt;colleagues&lt;/a&gt; will try to arrest the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;."}
