{"id": "40631", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40631", "title": "Vampiric Illithid", "text": "The Vampiric Illithid is a creature encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Illithid%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Illithid Encampment&lt;/a&gt; during or the games.\nGameplay.\nTo encounter this creature, the party must have the restored &lt;a href=\"Illithid%20Rod\"&gt;Illithid Rod&lt;/a&gt; in their possession, which serves as a key to open a door and enter a specific room in the Illithid Encampment.\nWithin the room are two alien looking stone-like \"pods\" with sealed slab doors.\nThere are also three circular stone fonts with odd decor, that are seemingly partially filled with some kind of deep crimson gelatinous ichor.\nWithin one of the fonts is found a &lt;a href=\"Red%20Oil\"&gt;Red Oil&lt;/a&gt; bottle. When a party member removes it (this item is needed in order to progress in Watcher's Keep), the two stone pods release a pair of these Vampiric Illithids, who are hostile and attack.\nExpect an initial &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Blast\"&gt;Psionic Blast&lt;/a&gt; attempt at the nearest detectable party member/enemy they can observe.\nThe creatures then will engage in attacks at close range to any detected intruder, using their tentacle attacks.\nRather than the feared Mind Flayer \"Devour Brain\" attack, their tentacles pierce and stab the flesh, tearing sinew and skin with each hit, and drawing out the life energy of the victim with a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effect. Simultaneously, the illithid is healed of up to 2d8 current hit point damage (with each successful hit).\nThese illithids have no elemental resistance, but they regenerate and have immunities typically afforded to the &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Vampire (Ancient)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party is able to destroy these monstrosities, the creatures morph into a gas cloud and flee the dungeon area. Perhaps to reform elsewhere.\nLore.\nAn Illithid vampire is regarded as insane even in the Mind Flayer society. This explains why the game has these creatures with a sub optimal intelligence attribute. See the external link below for more Dungeons and Dragons info about these horrors.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few revisions to this creature.\nIt's Hit Dice are raised to level 12, and 50% &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance is added.\nSaving throws are changed to 5/6/6/5/5.\nThe illithid has scripted use of several &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; powers, including \"Planar Travel\", Improved Invisibility, and the usual Psionic Blast.\nThe attack weapon utilized by this creature is the same as the unmodded version, except a hit also inflicts the \"Devour Brain\" effect as well as the level draining and healing, in accordance with the 2nd edition D&amp;D ruleset.\nAnd finally, a smarter AI is furnished to look for vulnerabilities and to select targets. The creature won't waste time trying an attack that won't work or can't hit and look for another target. The creature may even Planar Travel across several rooms to attack party members hidden away."}
{"id": "9077", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9077", "title": "Vampiric Mist", "text": "Vampiric Mists are undead monsters with the ability to drain levels. In areas where they are encountered, they will usually appear as a spawned creature, except for the seven encountered inside &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs%23Bodhi%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; during the events of .\nGameplay.\nThey are immune to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;, non-magical weapons, and can naturally see invisible or hidden creatures. They have 100% resistance to all forms of acid, cold, fire and poison damage.\nTheir elongated tentacle-like fingers are considered non-magical weapons with a +3 &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt;. This means that &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20Phasing\"&gt;Boots of Phasing&lt;/a&gt; will work against them, but not &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. The fingers deal 1d8 of either &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, whichever is best, and each successful hit will heal the Vampiric Mist by 4 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, with a 18% chance to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; one level from the target.\nThey use the &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell when driven below 50% HP and have a chance to reopen the fight with &lt;a href=\"Larloch%27s%20Minor%20Drain\"&gt;Larloch's Minor Drain&lt;/a&gt;. They can then reuse invisibility repeatedly until fully healed."}
{"id": "5027", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5027", "title": "Vampiric Touch", "text": "Vampiric Touch drains hit points from the target and temporarily adds them to the caster.\nGameplay.\nFor dual- and multi-classes, the bhaalspawn version of the spell scales with the average of their classes (rounded up).\nSince the bonus hit points last for 1 hour, this spell might also be used by characters before combat (e.g. on summons or on companions who get subsequently healed) to start combat with additional HP.\nThe spell is implemented as 2 spells in :\nThe spell is implemented as a single spell in the original edition of Baldur's Gate II. The extra hit points received by the caster are:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, scaling and duration. See below for description:\nVampiric Touch\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Touch\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the target loses 3 hit points for every two caster levels, to a maximum drain of 30 for a 20th level caster. These hit points are added to the caster\u2019s current hit points, with any hit points over the caster\u2019s normal maximum treated as temporary additional hit points. The temporary hit points last for 5 turns.\nNote that this spell may not be cast multiple times to radically increase the caster\u2019s hit points. The caster must wait for the first Vampiric Touch spell to run its course before casting another."}
{"id": "51396", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51396", "title": "Vampiric Touch (innate)", "text": "Vampiric Touch (innate) is an innate ability available to predominantly &lt;a href=\"Tanar%27ri\"&gt;Tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; demon creatures. It is also referred to as \"Tanar'ri Vampiric Touch\" in the script. The ability is initiated via script by the AI. \nEffects.\nThe effect is directed at a single creature, within detection range of the source creature and it is only applied to enemies in close quarters range.\nThe ability is force cast and cannot be interrupted or disrupted. \nThe Vampiric Touch has no saving throw and immediately applies a damage to the target. The effect is instantly applied and cannot be dispelled. Once the damage is applied, the caster receives a temporary Maximum Hit Point increase of 11, which lasts for 300 seconds. These extra hit points are non-magical and cannot be dispelled from the caster.\nIf affected by the ability, the party member will have a lighting effect displayed over their map animation and a sound effect will be played. \nVampiric Touch will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; but can be blocked by spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; and similar, as the internal Spell Power of the touch is level 3. As the ability is school-less and has no \"secondary type\", &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; or similar will have no interaction."}
{"id": "6956", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6956", "title": "Vampiric Wolf", "text": "The Vampiric Wolf is a rare and dangerous variety of &lt;a href=\"wolves\"&gt;wolves&lt;/a&gt; and is mainly encountered around the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;. It can only be harmed with &lt;a href=\"magical%20weapons\"&gt;magical weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, and it steals health from its targets when dealing &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt;, while potentially paralyzing them."}
{"id": "36248", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36248", "title": "Vampiric Wolf (Siege of Dragonspear)", "text": "A rare and dangerous variant of &lt;a href=\"wolves\"&gt;wolves&lt;/a&gt;, the vampiric wolf \u2013 as encountered throughout the \"\" \u2013 is not only capable of healing itself by &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;damaging&lt;/a&gt; its enemy's &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, the target may also find themselves being held by the attack.\nCompared to the &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Wolf\"&gt;variant&lt;/a&gt; found at other places, the attack has a higher &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;chance to hit&lt;/a&gt; and can inflict more damage \u2013 while on the other hand the self-healing effect may not be as strong, though this wolf has a slightly better overall constitution. Besides other immunities, it can't be hit with &lt;a href=\"normal%20weapons\"&gt;normal weapons&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47293", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47293", "title": "Vampiric Wraith", "text": "Vampiric Wraiths are encountered as scripted and random spawns in a few locations in and the .\nGameplay.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; wraith-mist is a more formidable variant of a &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Mist\"&gt;Vampiric Mist&lt;/a&gt;, and have all their abilities including draining levels, immunity to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;, non-magical weapons, and can naturally see invisible or hidden creatures. They are supposed to regenerate 2 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; per second under their permanent &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Weak Haste&lt;/a&gt;. See the Bugs section, below.\nIt has tendrils that are considered non-&lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapons with &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; +3. This means that &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt; will work against the attacks, but not &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe mist's tendrils inflict 2d4 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; plus 10 points of &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the hit also heals 4 hit points up to the wraith's maximum. There is also a 50% chance of exposing the target to a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effect. The level drain can only be prevented by immunity to that status effect, for example, with the &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Plane%20Protection\"&gt;Negative Plane Protection&lt;/a&gt; spell or wearing the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Power\"&gt;Amulet of Power&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature can \"forcecast\" the &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell on itself when damaged below 50% HP. While invisible, the script may have the creature launch a &lt;a href=\"Larloch%27s%20Minor%20Drain\"&gt;Larloch's Minor Drain&lt;/a&gt; at a nearby opponent, or to move away for a period of time (presumably to heal/reevaluate), or it might simply attack with its melee weapon from invisibility - these actions are scripted with some random probabilities. The Invisibility may be reapplied, as there is no limit to this spell's use by the wraith, but it probably won't survive very long due to its relatively fragile hit points. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default AI script for smarter tactical behavior. "}
