{"id": "7460", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7460", "title": "Vaxall", "text": "Vaxall is a &lt;a href=\"beholder\"&gt;beholder&lt;/a&gt; and a member of &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune\"&gt;Twisted Rune&lt;/a&gt;. When &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party accidently enter the &lt;a href=\"Twisted%20Rune%20Hideout\"&gt;Twisted Rune Hideout&lt;/a&gt;, they will be acknowledged by the lich &lt;a href=\"Shangalar\"&gt;Shangalar&lt;/a&gt;. After a brief declaration, the lich will call forth Vaxall and other available members to dispose of you - the intruders.\nVaxall has several potentially disabling, damaging and deadly beholder blast attacks, delivered as projectile rays from the many eye stalks protruding from the creature. The most notable of which is the beholder &lt;a href=\"Anti-Magic%20Ray\"&gt;Anti-Magic Ray&lt;/a&gt;. See the Info Box for the variety of beholder Rays, fired rapidly at a target, sometimes more than once per round.\nIts central &lt;a href=\"Beholder%20Eye\"&gt;eye&lt;/a&gt; is the key to the portal which will allow you to leave the hideout and return to Athkatla. \nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the creature, and the most apparent changes occur if you have installed the \"Smarter Beholders\" component. Obviously, the Beholder will be more intelligent, recognize threats and look for party vulnerabilities. It is actually an &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Orb\"&gt;Elder Orb&lt;/a&gt; now, with spell casting abilities and fully functional eye stalk powers. It will pursue party members and try to move out of gas clouds. Please go to the &lt;a href=\"Beholder\"&gt;Beholder&lt;/a&gt; article where the mod's revisions are detailed. The creature has all the immunities of the unmodded creature, plus listed below are Vaxall specific changes made by SCS:\nWith SCS Vaxall may open hostilities with a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; - then fire off a contingency with a triple conjuring including a &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Efreeti\"&gt;Summon Efreeti&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Djinni\"&gt;Summon Djinni&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt;, directed at the closest opponent in detection range. This will not break its invisibility.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, Vaxall's arcane magic will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "8209", "revid": "197828", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8209", "title": "Vay-ya", "text": "Vay-ya is one of two worshipers of entropy who can be found on the second level of the &lt;a href=\"Low%20Lantern\"&gt;Low Lantern&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; agrees to feel the pleasures of entropy, she and &lt;a href=\"Desreta\"&gt;Desreta&lt;/a&gt; will attack. If you tell them to scram, they'll oblige.\nGameplay.\nVay-ya will cycle through her entire spellbook before switching to melee attack with her &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "40296", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40296", "title": "Velithuu", "text": "The Velithuu is a unique demon found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Baatezu%20%28AR3004%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Baatezu (AR3004)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThe creature uses the &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Salamander\"&gt;Frost Salamander&lt;/a&gt; sprite as it's animation.\nThis demon has the racial enemy against &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt; opponents, a therefore receives a 4 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and damage bonus.\nThe creature has all the usual immunities of demons and can also &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature's AI primarily makes the demon fire it's shortbow at the closest target over 10 feet distant. \nBow fire is rapid with a good degree of skill, and an endless supply of ammunition is available for the equipped &lt;a href=\"Shortbow%20of%20Gesen\"&gt;Shortbow of Gesen&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf forced into melee combat by an opponent (achieved by getting into melee range and staying close to the demon) - then the creature switches attack weapons. The demon's slashing melee attack can &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; the target, but a saving throw is allowed. \nThe Velithuu can cast three Wizard spell types as shown on the InfoBox. \nNotes.\nThe potential use of Spirit Armor by the demon is actually counterproductive to the demon's defense, other than a saving throw bonus. It might even end up damaging itself after casting it.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes no special changes to this creature apart from adding immunity to &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;Webbed&lt;/a&gt; effects."}
{"id": "49602", "revid": "283963", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49602", "title": "Vellin Dahn", "text": "Vellin Dahn makes a brief appearance in the Dock of &lt;a href=\"Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt;'s tanning shop and home within the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. Vellin is a mage, and most probably affiliated with the Twisted Rune organization. He makes his getaway by magical means, and - depending on the protagonist's experience points - may summon &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Assassin\"&gt;Rune Assassin&lt;/a&gt;s and a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt; to delay your party - or even kill you. This is part of the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;\"Skinner\" Murders&lt;/a&gt; side-quest.\nVellin is never prone to being attacked, as the scripting ensures that he is not a viable target. There is no means to strike or cast spells before he vanishes."}
