{"id": "8897", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8897", "title": "Vhailor's Helm", "text": "Vhailor's Helm offers the wearer a bonus to armor class of -1, as well as the ability to use the wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt; once per day. It can be bought from &lt;a href=\"Deidre\"&gt;Deidre&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%27s%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer's Mart&lt;/a&gt;. See the &lt;a href=\"Exploits%23Clones\"&gt;Clones&lt;/a&gt; section of &lt;a href=\"Exploits\"&gt;Exploits&lt;/a&gt; to better understand the helmet's usefulness.\nThis helmet casts the actual &lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt; spell, meaning that the user's arcane caster level is utilized. However, the minimum programmed duration for Simulacrums is 16 rounds, so that's what characters with no (or too few) Mage levels get. Characters with more Mage/Bard levels can get a duration of up to 20 rounds, just like with the regular spell. \nTrivia.\n&lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Atorment%3AThe_Nameless_One\"&gt;The Nameless One&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Atorment%3AVhailor\"&gt;Vhailor&lt;/a&gt; are characters from &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Atorment\"&gt;Planescape: Torment&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"Gameplay Tweaks\" component moves Vhailor's Helm to . It is now worn by &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;, who is not afraid to use it."}
