{"id": "11082", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11082", "title": "Vial of Mysterious Liquid", "text": "A Vial of Mysterious Liquid is a bottle of a corrosive substance used to contaminate iron ore across the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It is found on the second level in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; in the possession of two &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s that are part of a group of four standing near the exit to the third level of the mine. This item is part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Tainted%20Ore\"&gt;The Tainted Ore&lt;/a&gt; quest, which was cut from the original game but restored for the \nDrinking it as a potion will cause the imbiber to become poisoned \u2014 effect is 1 damage per second over 20 seconds, for a maximum of 20 \"flat\" poison damage \u2014 as well as permanently lose one point of &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nThe quest can be restored for the original game by installing the mod &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG1\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG1&lt;/a&gt; by Pocket Plane."}
