{"id": "42988", "revid": "265597", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42988", "title": "Vidyadhar", "text": "Vidyadhar is a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; who can be met in \"\".\nEncounter.\nAs part of &lt;a href=\"Zaviak%27s%20Vision%20Quest\"&gt;Zaviak's Vision Quest&lt;/a&gt;, he can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, specifically in the storeroom just north of the entrance where you encounter &lt;a href=\"Gurgle%20and%20Floss\"&gt;Gurgle and Floss&lt;/a&gt;. If drawn into the material realm, he lectures the player on the folly of summoning powerful extraplanar beings, and then offers them the chance to gain a magical item if they can answer his riddle.\nIf correct answer is chosen or &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt; are asked to answer, he rewards the party with the &lt;a href=\"Modron%20Heart\"&gt;Modron Heart&lt;/a&gt; and then teleports away. If riddle is failed, he will attack.\nCombat.\nThis is an incredibly difficult fight. Upon combat beginning, his &lt;a href=\"Contingency\"&gt;Contingency&lt;/a&gt; will trigger a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; spell, which will generally give him time to get off his &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, which combined with natural non-magical immunity to normal weapons and spells of 7th level or less, makes him essentially invulnerable for 4 rounds, barring a successful &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;. During this time, he will cast &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt;, with a better than average chance of also hitting &lt;a href=\"Gurgle\"&gt;Gurgle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Floss\"&gt;Floss&lt;/a&gt;, if they are still alive. He also has a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and additional Stoneskin for defense.\nOnce reduced to half health, he will stop hostility, drop the Modron Heart, award , and then nearly instantly teleport away. While it is technically possible for a party with sufficiently high damage output can kill him before the teleport, it is fairly unlikely. Still, if accomplished, he will drop two additional items on death; a Scroll of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20from%20Magic\"&gt;Protection from Magic&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Scimitar%20%2B3\"&gt;Scimitar +3&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis spell immunity does not include from items such as Potion of Fire Breath, The Victor (ring) or Screaming Bagpipes (he is easily killed with several Potions of Fire Breath).\nTechnical notes.\nThe creature starts out with the &lt;a href=\"BDSPECTQ.ITM%20%28Invisible%29\"&gt;BDSPECTQ.ITM (Invisible)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"BDMISC1B.ITM%20%28Invulnerable%29\"&gt;BDMISC1B.ITM (Invulnerable)&lt;/a&gt;, which act to make it immune to nearly all actions, as well as give it the ghostly visual effect. When the Spectacles of Spectacle are used on it, both are destroyed."}
