{"id": "55331", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55331", "title": "Virah", "text": "Virah is in the \"employ\" of &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Nin\"&gt;Madame Nin&lt;/a&gt; in the Copper Coronet as an \"escort\".\nGameplay.\nVirah and a male client are in one of the back rooms. If a party member opens the door and enters, she will protest at the rude disturbance, and rightly so.\nWhat kind of a weirdo would barge into a private room with its door closed anyhow? The answer to that is the player's party of rude, non-conforming, felonious and ham-fisted adventurers.\nIf the party doesn't leave soon, or continues poking around in there, Virah will have another indignant remark.\nYou'll get one more warning to move on, and if not &lt;a href=\"Madame%20Nin\"&gt;Madame Nin&lt;/a&gt; will make an appearance to see what the ruckus is all about.\nIf the player tries to speak to Virah she'll say something in exasperated fashion about who let such idiots in here, and by idiots she means the party member.\nThere may be some amusing dialogue from &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; if he was the one who entered the room.\nHarming her counts as attacking an innocent, so expect up a -10 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss if she is killed."}
{"id": "8087", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8087", "title": "Visaj", "text": "Visaj is a drow mage who resides in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and will make up to two appearances in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter being asked to fetch blood of a neighboring race by the &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace&lt;/a&gt;, Visaj will spawn/appear on a city pathway between &lt;a href=\"Qilue%27s%20Home\"&gt;Qilue's Home&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Deirex's Tower&lt;/a&gt;, and protection from the lich within.\nWhen a party member is within a set distance, he will initiate dialogue.\nHe'll ask you to buy the &lt;a href=\"Gilded%20Rope\"&gt;Gilded Rope&lt;/a&gt; from him. A series of dialogue selections and choices will determine the outcome of the offer. Should the party obtain the magical rope the understanding is that this will allow entry to &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Deirex's Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party turns down Visaj's offer, he will say that if you change your mind to speak with him again - and Visaj just remains in this spot.\nVisaj is the initiator of getting that side quest &lt;a href=\"Intrigue%20with%20Jarlaxle\"&gt;Intrigue with Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt; underway, but it won't progress any further unless the party obtains the rope, and then enters the tower. More information about this is on the &lt;a href=\"Intrigue%20with%20Jarlaxle\"&gt;Intrigue with Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt; article. \nShould the party decide that attacking Visaj is something desired, note that this can certainly occur. If he's attacked before he initiates dialogue then Visaj will become hostile, as will the entire drow city. Likewise, if he's attacked after the party declines his offer to buy the rope, the same thing will happen.\nHowever, if the party attacks Visaj after obtaining the rope, then he won't turn hostile, and the city remains passive. After the party obtains the rope, Visaj walks away from the party and will eventually leave the map. During that period, he can be killed. \nOddly enough, if Visaj is killed - he'll still appear again with Jarlaxle later. No mention of his being killed will even be brought up in dialogue. This seems very bizarre indeed.\nIf the party elects to attack Visaj and Jarlaxle later in the Intrigue with Jaraxle quest, then the mage will defend himself and participate in battle using his spells."}
{"id": "56095", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56095", "title": "Vitality Drain (Aesgareth)", "text": "The Vitality Drain spell is cast by &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects.\nGameplay.\nWhen a party member character engages in a card draw contest with Aesgareth, the character must declare a wager. \nOne of the wager choices is \"Vitality\". Should the character lose the draw, then Aesgareth will collect on the wager, and the cambion's dialogue script implements a spell upon the character.\nThe spell manifests over the party member, with a lighting and sound effect, as well as a text displayed on the combat log reading \"Vitality Drain\".\nThe spell strips away 10% of the character's maximum HP modifier, permanently.\nFor example, if the character had a maximum HP value of 120, then this spell reduces it by 10%, or in this example, -12 HP. The new maximum HP modifier will be 108.\nThe second effect of this spell is that Aesgareth absorbs this vitality, and the fiend's maximum HP modifier is raised by 20. For example, Aesgareth has 150 HP. After this spell the cambion's HP is raised to 170, permanently.\nTake note that the maximum HP modifier change on a character doesn't do any immediate reduction to HP. However, damage incurred later and then subsequent healing/regeneration will reveal that the maximum HP ceiling has been lowered. \nThe spell is unaffected by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, as the spell is of the Necromancy School, it can be blocked by the appropriate &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; can also block it, as the spell is of the &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20damage%20type\"&gt;Offensive damage type&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnd finally, a spell protection may work as well, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, as the internal spell effect components have a 9 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player will know if any of those defensive measures work, as the combat log will display \"Spell Ineffective\" if it is neutered."}
{"id": "50304", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50304", "title": "Vithal", "text": "Vithal is a high-level human Conjurer that can be encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, but only if a specific action is taken as detailed in the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%20Imprisoned%3F\"&gt;A Mage Imprisoned?&lt;/a&gt; questline page. \nGameplay.\nAssuming the encounter takes place, another quest can be initiated, which is optional, and that is described in the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; page. \nVithal is not initially hostile to the party, and until some overt action or certain conditions are triggered in his subsequent questline, will only become hostile then.\nNote that this creature can be pick pocketed of certain items from his inventory, though initially there is only a quarterstaff and a random treasure on his person. \nOther items will be added to his inventory as he successfully exits each of the &lt;a href=\"Portals%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Portals (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the party to attempt to pickpocket the spoils from the other side. \nThe first &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; portal adds 5 scrolls to Vithal's inventory which can be taken (&lt;a href=\"Simulacrum\"&gt;Simulacrum&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Incendiary%20Cloud\"&gt;Incendiary Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wail%20of%20the%20Banshee\"&gt;Wail of the Banshee&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;). \nThe second &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt; portal then adds the &lt;a href=\"Rod%20of%20Absorption\"&gt;Rod of Absorption&lt;/a&gt;, which while it can be pickpocketed, will be rewarded to the party regardless at the end of this quest. \nLastly, the third &lt;a href=\"Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; portal will place the &lt;a href=\"Skull%20of%20Death\"&gt;Skull of Death&lt;/a&gt; within Vithal's belongings, which can itself be stolen either before or after claiming your reward from him, though you must be quick as he begins teleporting away upon completion of &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;the quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to this mage. First, the mage specialty kit may be changed an Invoker (or Conjurer, Enchanter or Necromancer - its random), with some different spells memorized, and a new default SCS script is assigned. \nInstallation of the \"Smarter Mages\" component, which is reactive to the game difficulty setting will determine if Vithal can use any of the Mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; he is assigned, including &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. Also, contingencies, spell triggers and sequencers are pre-loaded and will be used for near instant deployment of buffs and attacks. Vithal receives 1-point quarterstaff weapon proficiency. SCS adds a Mod only random treasure as well. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod will make all the memorized spells the SR versions.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; Mod can add a component to Vithal's script and dialogue that can introduce choices as part of the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; questline."}
{"id": "6844", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6844", "title": "Vitiare", "text": "Vitiare is a &lt;a href=\"Thief%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; with sticky hands who is encountered in the western &lt;a href=\"Gambling%20Tents%20%28Carnival%29\"&gt;gambling tent&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon entering the tent, he will walk towards &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party, boldly state that he is a master thief, then steal up to from the party. If one is not quick enough, he can disappear before getting the chance to retake the stolen gold. He won't appear again after the theft.\nHe can be killed without reputation loss.\nStrategy.\nArm the party with ranged weapons and enter the tent. Pause the game and direct a party member to walk up to Vitiare. Unpause and, when the party member has reached him, he will steal the from them. Pause the game again and attack him. Unpause and, if you are quick and effective enough, he will be dead before he can escape.\nAlternatively, simply attack him with a distance weapon before he approaches a party member, thereby making him aggressive and allowing the party to kill him without a time limit. Despite having a dagger he will not try to attack, but will run around the tent instead."}
{"id": "45619", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45619", "title": "Vittorio", "text": "Vittorio is a character in the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish%20Adventure\"&gt;Limited Wish Adventure&lt;/a&gt; side quest. \nGameplay.\nThe player is provided a scroll with instructions written upon it from the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish\"&gt;Limited Wish&lt;/a&gt; Djinni. Have dialogue with Vittorio to initiate the adventure.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can find him in front of &lt;a href=\"Delosar%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Delosar's Inn&lt;/a&gt;. He asks Gorion's Ward to collect money from &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt; who is within the Inn's second floor. If Captain Dennis is already dead because you previously killed him, then obviously this adventure is a shuttered and can't occur.\nIt turns out that he stole a gong from Dennis's mother when he taught him how to play the gong. He later sold the gong to &lt;a href=\"Roger%20the%20Fence\"&gt;Roger the Fence&lt;/a&gt; to fund his ale drinking spree. Dennis is angry about the theft and holds Vittorio until Gorion's Ward retrieve his gong. \nAnd so, the fetch quest can begin. The player can elect to not do this \"adventure\" if they wish. Companions such as Edwin and Viconia make it plain that they view this whole idea as pathetic and beneath the party's purpose. They could be right."}
{"id": "8633", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8633", "title": "Vivienne", "text": "Vivienne is a female commoner who is found on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Blushing%20Mermaid\"&gt;Blushing Mermaid&lt;/a&gt; in the room behind the bar that contains the only above ground entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Undercellar\"&gt;Undercellar&lt;/a&gt;. She will approach the party upon sight, asking them to save everyone from the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Crisis\"&gt;Iron Crisis&lt;/a&gt;. When the dialogue is finished, she will walk away and disappear.\nDialog.\n\"Please. *sniff* You must save us from this wretched iron!\""}
{"id": "6119", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6119", "title": "Vocalize", "text": "The Vocalize spell, by lore, allows a wizard to quietly cast spells with verbal components, by removing those verbal components. In truth, it is coded to act as a cure (and protection) from &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that you can cast it even after you were already silenced.\nRelated items.\nThe following items grant the vocalize effect while equipped (i.e., immunity to silence)"}
{"id": "14962", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14962", "title": "Voghiln", "text": "Voghiln is a neutral good human &lt;a href=\"Bard%23Skald\"&gt;skald&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in \nBackground.\nAn adventurer\u00a0from Luskan, also known as \"Voghiln the Mighty\" or \"Voghiln the Vast\".\nRecruitment.\nVoghiln\u00a0is available from Chapter 9, he can be found at the far north-eastern section of the &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Claw%20Woods\"&gt;Troll Claw Woods&lt;/a&gt; alongside &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"coordinates\"&gt;coordinates&lt;/a&gt;: x=3700, y=270). He will mistake you for a &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt;, but his &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; companion stops him before he can attack you. Jaheira then goes on to inform you about &lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt; being trapped in the &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;, which is under siege by &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar&lt;/a&gt;'s crusade. Even though he is traveling with Jaheira, the game doesn't require you to bring both of them along at the same time.\nGameplay.\nVoghiln is a versatile party member whose stats allow him to play many roles on the battlefield. By default he is equipped with &lt;a href=\"Voghiln%27s%20Helmet\"&gt;Voghiln's Helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20Defense%20AC%206\"&gt;Bracers of Defense AC 6&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"War%20Hammer%20%2B1\"&gt;Warhammer +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler +1&lt;/a&gt;, 40 &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axes +1&lt;/a&gt;, and 40 &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axe&lt;/a&gt;s. He also has 5 &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potions of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, 2 &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potions of Freedom&lt;/a&gt; and 1 &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mind%20Focusing\"&gt;Potion of Mind Focusing&lt;/a&gt;. As a bard, he is the only recruitable party member who can use bard-only magic items and equipment like musical instruments. His Skald Song gives every party member in reach +2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;to-hit&lt;/a&gt;, +2 dmg and +2 &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs a Skald, he has excellent &lt;a href=\"Lore\"&gt;Lore&lt;/a&gt; progression, making him perfect for identifying magic items on the cheap, but pitiful pickpocketing, to the point where it hardly matters what his Dexterity is. If you need him to pickpocket a target, give him at least one &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Master%20Thievery\"&gt;Potion of Master Thievery&lt;/a&gt; to drink first. His Charisma is low for a Bard but can be boosted by the &lt;a href=\"Friends\"&gt;Friends&lt;/a&gt; spell, whether by casting from his spell book or &lt;a href=\"Brevin%27s%20Quarterstaff\"&gt;Brevin's Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt; as a charge ability, making him an excellent party leader when shopping.\nRecommended equipment: \nHis initial &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiencies&lt;/a&gt; are:\nHe knows the following spells at recruitment:&lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt; (stun), &lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Invisibility%2010%27%20Radius\"&gt;Invisibility 10' Radius&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20Weapon\"&gt;Enchanted Weapon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;\n\nVoghiln - this time under the title \"Voghiln the Vast\" - reappears as one of the gladiators in the new Black Pits.\nPersonality.\nVoghiln is stereotypical Viking-type: He loves to drink, he loves to fight and loves to have beautiful women around him. Ideally all at once. All of that is crowned with an over-the-top Saxon accent. And let's not forget that he likes speaking of himself in third person. Underneath his rude behavior and his inability to be faithful however, lurks a funny and charming fellow who's got his heart in the right place."}
